#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Project BL9 Intel - Part 1 - Our Organization"
msgid_plural "Project BL9 Intel - Part 1 - Our Organizations"
msgstr[0] "BL9计划情报 - 第一部分 - 我们的组织"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'Project BL9 Intel - Part 1 - Our Organization'}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"We represent a secret organization that has existed pre-Cataclysm as well. Our current goals are researching peculiar alien microorganisms, minerals, gases and liquids. Also, no doubt, one of our top priorities is finding efficient ways to survive, restore our former main hub's glory. A dream of ours to make some kind of a safe place for people to live, work, love each other in as well.\n"
" \n"
"    It will take a lot of time, especially with fending off these invaders, dealing with other microorganisms, like Mycus, Triffids, and experimenting on mutations to possibly find a way to counter The Blob somehow"
msgstr ""
"我们代表着一个在大灾变前就已存在的秘密组织。我们当前的目标是研究奇特的外星微生物、矿物、气体和液体。同时，毫无疑问，我们的首要任务之一便是寻找有效的生存方式，恢复我们昔日主枢纽的荣光。我们的梦想是打造某种安全之地，让人们能在其中生活、工作、彼此相爱。\n"
"\n"
"    这将耗费大量时间，尤其是在抵御这些入侵者、应对其他微生物（如真菌、三裂植物）以及进行突变实验以可能找到某种对抗粘液团的方法的过程中。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Project BL9 Intel - Part 2 - Our Organization's Goals"
msgid_plural "Project BL9 Intel - Part 2 - Our Organization's Goalss"
msgstr[0] "BL9计划情报 - 第二部分 - 我们组织的目标"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Project BL9 Intel - Part 2 - Our Organization's
#. Goals"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"We specialize in research in terms of learning about inner structure and uses of peculiar alien microorganisms, minerals, gases and liquids. This also includes The Blob, Mycus, Triffids. Newest one that we research more diligently is BL9, because out of all of them, BL9 is the most unique, flexible. Based on initial experiments, it is pretty easy to affect and alter, change it's structure.\n"
" \n"
"    It's unique abilities can lead to horrible mutations or possibly some kind of a cure or protection from other microorganisms as well"
msgstr ""
"我们专注于研究奇特外星微生物、矿物、气体和液体的内部结构及用途。这包括粘液团、真菌、三裂植物。我们最新且更深入研究的是BL9，因为在所有研究对象中，BL9是最独特、最灵活的。基于初步实验，它相当容易影响和改变，其结构可被调整。\n"
"\n"
"    它独特的能力可能导致可怕的突变，也可能带来某种治愈方法或对其他微生物的防护。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Project BL9 Intel - Part 3 - What is BL9?"
msgid_plural "Project BL9 Intel - Part 3 - What is BL9?s"
msgstr[0] "BL9计划情报 - 第三部分 - 什么是BL9？"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'Project BL9 Intel - Part 3 - What is BL9?'}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"It's a sentient, very intelligent alien symbiote that has managed to appear on Earth via a space warp gate, portals on Earth, fallen meteorites even. It's only way of survival is via finding a host, causing a symbiosis. Symbiosis, depending on many factors, can vary. Now, said factors can be personalities of hosts, type of BL9 it is, whether BL9's structure was artificially changed, modified in a particular way.\n"
" \n"
"    Symbiosis can be benign and even protective, granting it's host great powers, protection. But if symbiote is modified in a particular way it can also lead to all kinds of incredible mutations that can turn hosts almost feral, aggressive yet obedient at the same time pretty much. Latter is something that 'THEY' often utilize to create an army of almost mindless aggressive obedient mutants as well"
msgstr ""
"它是一种有感知力、高度智能的外星共生体，通过空间扭曲门、地球上的传送门，甚至坠落的陨石出现在地球上。它唯一的生存方式是寻找宿主，引发共生。共生关系根据多种因素而变化。这些因素包括宿主的个性、BL9的类型，以及BL9的结构是否被人工改变、以特定方式改造。\n"
"\n"
"    共生可以是良性的，甚至是保护性的，赋予宿主强大的力量与防护。但如果共生体以特定方式被改造，也可能导致各种不可思议的突变，使宿主几乎变得野蛮、具有攻击性，但同时仍相当服从。后者正是“他们”常用来创造一支近乎无脑、具有攻击性且服从的突变体军队的手段。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Printed 'THEIR' Soldier's Journal - Our Master's Grand Scheme"
msgid_plural "Printed 'THEIR' Soldier's Journal - Our Master's Grand Schemes"
msgstr[0] "打印的“他们”士兵日志 - 我们主人的宏伟计划"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Printed 'THEIR' Soldier's Journal - Our Master's
#. Grand Scheme"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"We are led by one of the brightest minds that exists during our times. The only way to rebuild this world is to create disciplined, fully obedient people, that will not dare to question our leadership, ranging from regular civilians to physically enhanced soldiers and even mutated amalgamations to use as our elite soldiers. With BL9 that's very much possible. These who will not bow down to us to accept us as leaders will be forced to infuse themselves with our own modified version of BL9\n"
" \n"
"    Also, based on BL9's properties, it counters The Blob, Triffids, Mycus entirely. This in addition to the fact that it's absolutely benign, hardly a weapon, but with a few tweaks, of course, it can be turned into a true weapon. With huge amounts of resources, weapons, materials, workforce including scientists and engineers, we can expand as an organization. Maybe even assert dominance across local areas. With more hosts, maybe even across entire country, possibly even across the world"
msgstr ""
"我们由当今时代最杰出的头脑之一领导。重建这个世界的唯一途径，是培养纪律严明、绝对服从的人民，他们不敢质疑我们的领导，从普通平民到身体强化的士兵，甚至变异融合体，都将作为我们的精英士兵。借助BL9，这完全可能实现。那些不愿臣服于我们、不接受我们领导的人，将被强制注入我们改良版的BL9。\n"
"\n"
"此外，基于BL9的特性，它能完全对抗The Blob、Triffids和Mycus。再加上它本身绝对无害，几乎算不上武器，但经过一些调整，当然可以转变为真正的武器。凭借大量资源、武器、材料、劳动力（包括科学家和工程师），我们可以扩展组织规模。甚至可能在局部地区确立统治地位。随着宿主增多，或许能覆盖整个国家，甚至全世界。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Project BL9 Intel - Part 4 - 'THEY'"
msgid_plural "Project BL9 Intel - Part 4 - 'THEY's"
msgstr[0] "BL9项目情报 - 第四部分 - '他们'"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Project BL9 Intel - Part 4 - 'THEY'"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"Hmm, 'THEY' is a hostile organization to us. They utilize The Blob, Mycus, "
"Triffids, BL9 in horrendous and inhumane ways. Their main goal is to create "
"an army of obedient mutants, with an intention of conquering local areas "
"first and then entire Earth, creating a 'New Order' of some sorts. They "
"strive to have all civilians, mutants infused with BL9, for them to be "
"entirely obedient to their leader and mastermind of some sorts. Whoever this"
" person is, that's a madman in reality pretty much"
msgstr ""
"嗯，'他们'是一个对我们怀有敌意的组织。他们以可怕且不人道的方式利用The "
"Blob、Mycus、Triffids和BL9。他们的主要目标是建立一支服从的突变体军队，意图先征服局部地区，然后统治整个地球，建立某种'新秩序'。他们竭力让所有平民和突变体都注入BL9，使其完全服从于他们的领袖和某种幕后主使。无论这个人是谁，实际上都是个疯子。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Printed Cultist's Journal - Our Deity's Powerful Blood"
msgid_plural "Printed Cultist's Journal - Our Deity's Powerful Bloods"
msgstr[0] "印刷版邪教徒日志 - 我们神祇的强大之血"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Printed Cultist's Journal - Our Deity's Powerful
#. Blood"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"This strange liquified being, it gives inhumane powers to whoever consumes it. Our miners in mines of our Great Castlelan's Creation managed to find it. Some consumed it instantly out of curiousity they had. It killed ones who were not worthy of our Deity's magnificent blessing, but it gave incredible powers to ones worthy of it.\n"
" \n"
"    We believe this to be a blood of our Deity, a blessing given to us. These are means to mark us as worthy warriors to destroy heretics, anyone who opposes creation of New World, who disregards our beliefs, who presumes us to be madmen. We must fight fools and obstacles on our way, our vile enemies"
msgstr ""
"这种奇异的液化存在，赋予任何饮用者非人的力量。我们伟大Castlelan造物矿井中的矿工设法找到了它。一些人出于好奇立刻饮下。它杀死了那些不配获得我们神祇宏伟祝福的人，却赐予了配得上的人难以置信的力量。\n"
"\n"
"我们相信这是我们神祇的血液，是赐予我们的祝福。这些是标记我们为合格战士的手段，以消灭异端、任何反对新世界创造、无视我们信仰、视我们为疯子的人。我们必须与途中的愚者和障碍、我们卑劣的敌人战斗。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Project BL9 Intel - Part 5 - Castlelan's Cult"
msgid_plural "Project BL9 Intel - Part 5 - Castlelan's Cults"
msgstr[0] "BL9项目情报 - 第五部分 - Castlelan的邪教"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Project BL9 Intel - Part 5 - Castlelan's Cult"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"Hmm, 'Cult' is a moderately spread occult group led by this strange man, living in a gigantic Castle with essentially a countless amount of servants, in isolation. They practice horrible occult beliefs with human sacrifices, cleansing one's blood with barely edible and strange things and drugs that they produce themselves. Based on various rumors, they are even practicing cannibalism, but not exactly sure, to be honest.\n"
" \n"
"    They have allied with 'THEM' in exchange for more advanced BL9 samples that Castlelan has already come across and started to forcefully infuse his servants with. They believe that BL9 is a blood or remnant of some sorts of their chaotic war deity, valuable sign for them"
msgstr ""
"嗯，'邪教'是一个由这个怪人领导、传播范围中等的隐秘团体，居住在一座巨大的城堡中，拥有几乎无数的仆人，与世隔绝。他们奉行可怕的隐秘信仰，包括人祭、用几乎不可食用的奇怪物品和自产药物净化血液。根据各种传闻，他们甚至实行食人，但老实说，不太确定。\n"
"\n"
"他们与'他们'结盟，以换取更先进的BL9样本，Castlelan已经接触并开始强制给仆人注入。他们相信BL9是他们混沌战争神祇的血液或某种遗物，对他们来说是宝贵的标志。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Project BL9 Intel - Part 6 - Biomes"
msgid_plural "Project BL9 Intel - Part 6 - Biomess"
msgstr[0] "BL9项目情报 - 第六部分 - 生物群落"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'Project BL9 Intel - Part 6 - Biomes'}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"Biomes, so we call these areas of meteorites' impact. Apparently, not only BL9 but other various alien microorganisms, minerals, liquids and gases have entered soils and Earth's atmosphere in places of impact as well. This resulted in pollutions and creation of strangely colored biomes. A lot of valuable materials can be salvaged from there.\n"
" \n"
"    However, we are not the only ones who seek them and these places are quite infested with peculiar creatures as well"
msgstr ""
"生物群落，我们如此称呼这些陨石撞击区域。显然，不仅是BL9，其他各种外星微生物、矿物、液体和气体也进入了撞击点的土壤和地球大气层。这导致了污染和奇特颜色生物群落的形成。那里可以回收许多有价值的材料。\n"
"\n"
"然而，我们并非唯一寻求这些材料的人，这些地方也充斥着奇特的生物。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Project BL9 Intel - Part 7 - What Kind of Biomes Are There?"
msgid_plural "Project BL9 Intel - Part 7 - What Kind of Biomes Are There?s"
msgstr[0] "BL9项目情报 - 第七部分 - 有哪些类型的生物群落？"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'Project BL9 Intel - Part 7 - What Kind of Biomes
#. Are There?'}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"Well, there are former facilities that we know about with alien fauna along with mutants, however there are also lesser known much more dangerous cave biomes systems hidden beneath fortification towers of 'True Superiors' who seem to be friendly not only with Cult along with 'THEM' but also with 'Alliance' as well. All kinds of dangerous alien creatures inhabit each of them. These include mutated animal types, insectoids, weird mutated creatures, soldiers of 'True Superiors', advanced alien civilizations as well.\n"
" \n"
"    Now, most dangerous ones are advanced aliens' mobile bases, where we should not venture until we are strong enough physically, in terms of our equipment, weapons to handle these pillagers. 'Alliance', that's how they call themselves"
msgstr ""
"嗯，有我们已知的、存在外星动物群和突变体的前设施，但也有鲜为人知、更危险的洞穴生物群落系统，隐藏在'真正上位者'的防御塔下，他们似乎不仅与邪教和'他们'友好，还与'联盟'交好。各种危险的外星生物栖息于其中。包括突变动物类型、昆虫类、奇怪的突变生物、'真正上位者'的士兵，以及先进的外星文明。\n"
"\n"
"目前，最危险的是先进外星人的移动基地，在我们身体足够强壮、装备和武器足以应对这些掠夺者之前，不应冒险进入。'联盟'，他们如此自称。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Project BL9 Intel - Part 8 - Inhravtidius Species"
msgid_plural "Project BL9 Intel - Part 8 - Inhravtidius Speciess"
msgstr[0] "BL9项目情报 - 第八部分 - Inhravtidius物种"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'Project BL9 Intel - Part 8 - Inhravtidius
#. Species'}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"These alien species are native to a beautiful water planet of Davranides. Inhravtidius resemble crustacean-like creatures, they breed and live in caves, corrals of this planet. They have a thick curved carapace, 2 antennas protruding from their heads, multiple eyes, quickly moving tiny legs and 2 sharp and spiked pincers.\n"
" \n"
"    Obviously, Davranides have brought them here. Possibly for using them as experimental subjects for infusing with BL9, since it is the main reason 'Alliance' is here. We must approach them carefully. If they are infused with BL9 then many of them must have mutated as well"
msgstr ""
"这些外星物种原生于美丽的Davranides水行星。Inhravtidius类似甲壳类生物，它们在这个星球的洞穴和珊瑚中繁殖生活。它们有厚而弯曲的甲壳，头部伸出2根触角，多只眼睛，快速移动的小腿和2只尖锐带刺的钳子。\n"
"\n"
"显然，Davranides将它们带到了这里。可能是为了将它们用作注入BL9的实验对象，因为这是'联盟'在此的主要原因。我们必须小心接近它们。如果它们注入了BL9，那么许多个体很可能也已突变。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Project BL9 Intel - Part 9 - Yengnutrium Species"
msgid_plural "Project BL9 Intel - Part 9 - Yengnutrium Speciess"
msgstr[0] "BL9项目情报 - 第九部分 - Yengnutrium物种"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'Project BL9 Intel - Part 9 - Yengnutrium
#. Species'}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"These alien species are native to a swamp-like shrouded by glowing purple fog of some sorts planet of Arganoides. Yengnutrium are insectoids, resembling a strange mix of mantises and locusts, they breed and live in dryer underground cave systems of this planet. They have an elongated body, 2 antennas protruding from their heads, multiple eyes, many of them may have wings and 2 sharp serrated claws.\n"
" \n"
"    Obviously, Arganoides have brought them here. Possibly for using them as experimental subjects for infusing with BL9, since it is the main reason 'Alliance' is here. We must approach them carefully. If they are infused with BL9 then many of them must have mutated as well"
msgstr ""
"这些外星物种原生于Arganoides星球，一个笼罩在某种发光紫色雾气中的沼泽般世界。Yengnutrium是昆虫类，类似螳螂和蝗虫的奇怪混合体，它们在这个星球较干燥的地下洞穴系统中繁殖生活。它们有细长的身体，头部伸出2根触角，多只眼睛，许多个体可能有翅膀和2只尖锐锯齿状的爪子。\n"
"\n"
"显然，Arganoides将它们带到了这里。可能是为了将它们用作注入BL9的实验对象，因为这是'联盟'在此的主要原因。我们必须小心接近它们。如果它们注入了BL9，那么许多个体很可能也已突变。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Project BL9 Intel - Part 10 - Ulniviunite Species"
msgid_plural "Project BL9 Intel - Part 10 - Ulniviunite Speciess"
msgstr[0] "BL9项目情报 - 第十部分 - Ulniviunite物种"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'Project BL9 Intel - Part 10 - Ulniviunite
#. Species'}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"These alien species are native to a beautiful and dense jungle-like wildforests planet of Wanzeltiums. Ulniviunite are pangolin-like creatures, they breed and live in sandy cave areas located on shores of this planet. They have a body covered with slime, coated thick and durable scales, underbelly and tail grotesquely fleshy and slimy, lamprey-type mouth with a menacingly looking set of teeth, long anteater-like tongue along with incredibly thick and sturdy claws on the end of it's limbs.\n"
" \n"
"    Obviously, Wanzeltiums have brought them here. Possibly for using them as experimental subjects for infusing with BL9, since it is the main reason 'Alliance' is here. We must approach them carefully. If they are infused with BL9 then many of them must have mutated as well"
msgstr ""
"这些外星物种原生于美丽的Wanzeltiums星球，一个茂密丛林般的野生森林世界。Ulniviunite是穿山甲般的生物，它们在这个星球海岸边的沙质洞穴区域繁殖生活。它们的身体覆盖着黏液，披着厚实耐用的鳞片，腹部和尾巴 grotesquely fleshy and slimy，七鳃鳗型的嘴配有一副狰狞的牙齿，长如食蚁兽的舌头，以及四肢末端极其粗壮坚固的爪子。\n"
"\n"
"显然，Wanzeltiums将它们带到了这里。可能是为了将它们用作注入BL9的实验对象，因为这是'联盟'在此的主要原因。我们必须小心接近它们。如果它们注入了BL9，那么许多个体很可能也已突变。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Project BL9 Intel - Part 11 - Ezrondium Species"
msgid_plural "Project BL9 Intel - Part 11 - Ezrondium Speciess"
msgstr[0] "BL9项目情报 - 第十一部分 - Ezrondium物种"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'Project BL9 Intel - Part 11 - Ezrondium
#. Species'}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"These alien species are native to a volcanic canyons barren wasteland-like planet of Saldeniums. Ezrondium are arachnides resembling gigantic spiders, they breed and live in sandy cave areas located on shores of this planet. They have an enormous body from belly of which emerges a small worm-like protrusion, incredibly sharp and deadly looking elongated legs.\n"
" \n"
"    Obviously, Saldeniums have brought them here. Possibly for using them as experimental subjects for infusing with BL9, since it is the main reason 'Alliance' is here. We must approach them carefully. If they are infused with BL9 then many of them must have mutated as well"
msgstr ""
"这些外星物种原生于Saldeniums星球，一个火山峡谷般的贫瘠荒地世界。Ezrondium是类似巨型蜘蛛的蛛形纲生物，它们在这个星球海岸边的沙质洞穴区域繁殖生活。它们有巨大的身体，腹部伸出一个蠕虫般的小突起，极其尖锐且致命的长腿。\n"
"\n"
"显然，Saldeniums将它们带到了这里。可能是为了将它们用作注入BL9的实验对象，因为这是'联盟'在此的主要原因。我们必须小心接近它们。如果它们注入了BL9，那么许多个体很可能也已突变。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Project BL9 Intel - Part 12 - Advanced Alien Civilizations"
msgid_plural "Project BL9 Intel - Part 12 - Advanced Alien Civilizationss"
msgstr[0] "BL9项目情报 - 第十二部分 - 先进外星文明"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'Project BL9 Intel - Part 12 - Advanced Alien
#. Civilizations'}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"They call themselves 'Alliance', an alien alliance of Earth pillagers that "
"consists of 4 alien tribes from different planets. Each is a former savage, "
"but they have managed to turn into actual advanced alien civilizations with "
"the help of unique energy sources on their planets. Essentially they have "
"learned to form materials out of this energy. This includes advanced craft "
"materials, a type of a fuel. They have even learned to use it as weapons, "
"conjuring energy mass to use against their enemies. They are Arganoides, "
"Wanzeltiums, Davranides, Saldeniums as well"
msgstr ""
"他们自称'联盟'，一个由来自不同星球的4个外星部落组成的地球掠夺者外星联盟。每个部落都曾是野蛮人，但借助各自星球上的独特能源，他们成功转变为真正的先进外星文明。本质上，他们学会了用这种能量制造材料。这包括先进的工艺材料和一种燃料。他们甚至学会了将其用作武器，召唤能量团攻击敌人。他们分别是Arganoides、Wanzeltiums、Davranides和Saldeniums。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Project BL9 Intel - Part 13 - Native Planets of 'Alliance'"
msgid_plural "Project BL9 Intel - Part 13 - Native Planets of 'Alliance's"
msgstr[0] "BL9项目情报 - 第十三部分 - '联盟'的母星"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Project BL9 Intel - Part 13 - Native Planets of
#. 'Alliance'"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"Well, Arganoides are native to a swamp-like shrouded by purple fog of some "
"sorts planet. Wanzeltiums are native to a beatiful and dense jungle-like "
"wildforests planet. Davranides are native to a beautiful water planet. "
"Saldeniums are native to a volcanic barren wasteland-like planet. Humanoids,"
" indeed, but are all entirely different compared to each other"
msgstr ""
"嗯，Arganoides原生于一个笼罩在某种紫色雾气中的沼泽般星球。Wanzeltiums原生于一个美丽茂密的丛林般野生森林星球。Davranides原生于一个美丽的水行星。Saldeniums原生于一个火山贫瘠荒地般的星球。都是类人生物，但彼此之间完全不同。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Project BL9 Intel - Part 14 - 'Alliance' and It's Motives"
msgid_plural "Project BL9 Intel - Part 14 - 'Alliance' and It's Motivess"
msgstr[0] "BL9项目情报 - 第十四部分 - '联盟'及其动机"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Project BL9 Intel - Part 14 - 'Alliance' and
#. It's Motives"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"It's an alliance of alien invaders. These are 3 of them, Arganoides, Wanzeltiums, Davranides alien civilizations. There was one more, Saldeniums alien civilization, but they were too bloodthirsty to build mutually beneficial relations with someone so they were disposed of thanks to combined effort of other alien invaders alliance members which are definitely much more civilized. Their main reason of allying is supporting each other for successful survival on ravaged Earth, considering presence of all these hostile creatures here. Most important thing to them is BL9, they are obsessed with it, they seek it diligently.\n"
" \n"
"    They've learned, thanks to Davranides' research, that alien symbiotes are capable of granting their hosts incredible abilities. They've learned that BL9 is incredibly advanced, capable of being greatly modified. They've somehow learned that it is present on Earth, likely with their spy drones or portal spy teams, this is why they're here as well"
msgstr ""
"这是一个外星入侵者联盟。其中有三个文明：Arganoides、Wanzeltiums、Davranides外星文明。原本还有一个Saldeniums外星文明，但他们过于嗜血，无法与任何人建立互利关系，因此被其他外星入侵者联盟成员联手清除，这些成员无疑文明得多。他们结盟的主要原因是相互支持，以在满目疮痍的地球上成功生存，考虑到这里所有敌对生物的存在。对他们最重要的是BL9，他们对此着迷，孜孜不倦地寻找它。\n"
"\n"
"通过Davranides的研究，他们了解到外星共生体能够赋予宿主不可思议的能力。他们发现BL9极其先进，能够被大幅修改。他们不知何故得知它存在于地球上，可能是通过间谍无人机或传送间谍小队，这也是他们来到此地的原因。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Project BL9 Intel - Part 15 - 'Alliance' and It's Energy Sources"
msgid_plural ""
"Project BL9 Intel - Part 15 - 'Alliance' and It's Energy Sourcess"
msgstr[0] "BL9项目情报 - 第十五部分 - '联盟'及其能源"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Project BL9 Intel - Part 15 - 'Alliance' and
#. It's Energy Sources"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"Honestly, it's nowhere to be found when they've created their civilizations. Still, presence of hostile fauna, pretty harsh environmental conditions, all of this kind of makes an assumption that this would have hindered their progress sufficiently. What gave them so much strength is that they've found a unique source of energy on each of their planets.\n"
" \n"
"    In main journal we have already explained how they've used it to evolve from savages. However, it also boosts their physical capabilities. Crystalline glow that they have is due to their high consumption of this energy. They have become addicted to it, even with all advancements of theirs, they run out of this energy supply. They seek BL9 for this reason as well"
msgstr ""
"老实说，在他们创建文明之初，这种能源无处可寻。然而，敌对动物群的存在、相当恶劣的环境条件，所有这些都让人推测这会严重阻碍他们的进步。赋予他们如此强大力量的是，他们在各自星球上发现了一种独特的能源。\n"
"\n"
"在主日志中，我们已经解释了他们是怎样利用它从野蛮人进化而来。然而，它也增强了他们的身体能力。他们身上的晶体光芒是由于大量消耗这种能量所致。他们对此上瘾，即使拥有所有先进技术，这种能源供应也会耗尽。他们寻找BL9也是出于这个原因。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Project BL9 Intel - Part 16 - Arganoides Civilization"
msgid_plural "Project BL9 Intel - Part 16 - Arganoides Civilizations"
msgstr[0] "BL9项目情报 - 第十六部分 - Arganoides文明"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'Project BL9 Intel - Part 16 - Arganoides
#. Civilization'}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"Well, Arganoides are adventurers, explorers, mercenaries in general. They are native to a swamp-like shrouded by purple fog of some sorts planet. They are proficient at tracking, searching for anything that they consider valuable, it is their greatest skill.\n"
" \n"
"    They are tall graceful humanoid beings, emitting bright purple crystalline light. It's head resembles a water shaped droplet with hair-like long tentacles growing out of it, it has elongated eyes as well"
msgstr ""
"嗯，Arganoides通常是冒险家、探索者和雇佣兵。他们原生于一个笼罩在某种紫色雾气中的沼泽般星球。他们擅长追踪、寻找任何他们认为有价值的东西，这是他们最出色的技能。\n"
"\n"
"他们是高大优雅的类人生物，散发出明亮的紫色晶体光芒。头部类似水滴形状，长出发丝般的长触手，还有细长的眼睛。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Project BL9 Intel - Part 17 - Wanzeltiums Civilization"
msgid_plural "Project BL9 Intel - Part 17 - Wanzeltiums Civilizations"
msgstr[0] "BL9项目情报 - 第十七部分 - Wanzeltiums文明"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'Project BL9 Intel - Part 17 - Wanzeltiums
#. Civilization'}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"Well, Wanzeltiums are builders, engineers, craftsmen in general. They are native to a beautiful and dense jungle-like wildforests planet. They are masters of creating magnificent structures, ingeniously made tech, sturdy and durable armor along with strong weapons, it is their greatest skill.\n"
" \n"
"    They are over 5'8 feet tall reptile-like humanoids, emitting a bright green crystalline light. It has a reptilian-humanoid head having a greatly widened forehead covered with multiple thick skin lines, multiple hair-like spiky protrusions coming out of the back and sides of it's head, having wide eyes as well"
msgstr ""
"万泽尔蒂姆族是建造者、工程师，广义上的工匠。他们原生于一个美丽而茂密的类丛林野生森林星球。他们是创造宏伟建筑、精巧科技、坚固耐用护甲与强力武器的大师，这是他们最卓越的技能。\n"
"\n"
"    他们是身高超过5英尺8英寸的类爬虫人形生物，散发着明亮的绿色晶体光芒。拥有爬虫类人形头部，前额异常宽阔，覆盖着多条厚皮纹，头后部及两侧伸出多根毛发状的尖刺突起，眼睛也十分宽大。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Project BL9 Intel - Part 18 - Davranides Civilization"
msgid_plural "Project BL9 Intel - Part 18 - Davranides Civilizations"
msgstr[0] "BL9项目情报 - 第18部分 - 达夫拉尼德斯文明"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'Project BL9 Intel - Part 18 - Davranides
#. Civilization'}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"Well, Davranides are scientists, researchers, very professional keepers of scientific knowledge in general. They are native to a beautiful water planet. They research microorganisms, splice them, produce drugs, experiment with mutagens, symbiotes, all of this is something that they are very skilled at.\n"
" \n"
"    They are average height smooth-skinned amphibian-like humanoids, emitting a bright azure-blue crystalline light. It has an elongated cranium with eyes that protrude from each side of it's head on short stalks, they often have a calculating gaze as well"
msgstr ""
"达夫拉尼德斯族是科学家、研究者，广义上非常专业的科学知识守护者。他们原生于一个美丽的水行星。他们研究微生物、进行基因拼接、生产药物、实验诱变剂与共生体，所有这些领域他们都极为擅长。\n"
"\n"
"    他们是中等身高、皮肤光滑的类两栖人形生物，散发着明亮的天蓝色晶体光芒。拥有细长的头骨，眼睛通过短柄从头部两侧突出，目光常带有算计的意味。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Project BL9 Intel - Part 19 - Saldeniums Civilization"
msgid_plural "Project BL9 Intel - Part 19 - Saldeniums Civilizations"
msgstr[0] "BL9项目情报 - 第19部分 - 萨尔德尼姆文明"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'Project BL9 Intel - Part 19 - Saldeniums
#. Civilization'}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"Well, Saldeniums are incredibly strong warriors, hunters, mercenaries in general. They are native to a volcanic barren wasteland-like planet. On their planet they wage wars, conquer tribes, hunt animals. In space they hunt people in cases of mercenaries, teach other combat, all of this is something that they are very proficient at.\n"
" \n"
"    Because of their savage ways, upon providing combat training to allies of theirs which was the main reason of them being accepted in first place, thanks to support of Arganoides along with pragmatism of Wanzeltiums along with devious ways of Davranides civilizations, they have been expelled from their alliance justly. They evidently objected, but having taught others everything, having no industry, having no less savage, more practical merits of their own, they've become a liability, thrown back to their own planet"
msgstr ""
"萨尔德尼姆族是极其强大的战士、猎人，广义上的雇佣兵。他们原生于一个火山遍布的类荒芜废土星球。在他们的星球上，他们发动战争、征服部落、狩猎动物。在太空中，作为雇佣兵时他们追猎人类，教授他人战斗技巧，所有这些领域他们都极为精通。\n"
"\n"
"    由于他们的野蛮作风，尽管曾为盟友提供战斗训练（这也是他们最初被接纳的主要原因），但在阿尔加诺伊德族的支持、万泽尔蒂姆族的实用主义以及达夫拉尼德斯文明的诡诈手段共同作用下，他们被公正地驱逐出了联盟。他们显然表示反对，但既然已将所有技艺传授他人，自身缺乏工业基础，又没有比野蛮行径更实际的优点，他们最终成了累赘，被遣返回自己的星球。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Project BL9 Intel - Part 20 - What 'Alliance' Wants To Do With BL9?"
msgid_plural ""
"Project BL9 Intel - Part 20 - What 'Alliance' Wants To Do With BL9?s"
msgstr[0] "BL9项目情报 - 第20部分 - “联盟”想用BL9做什么？"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Project BL9 Intel - Part 20 - What 'Alliance'
#. Wants To Do With BL9?"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"Honestly, Arganoides are interested mainly in using it as a high quality fuel for their spaceships, more efficient locating tech for acquiring rare valuable items. Wanzeltiums want to use it for creating more durable and unique building materials, improving their existing tech and weapons via infusing it with BL9.\n"
" \n"
"    Davranides crave to significantly advance their existent mutation, splicing research in an attempt to make their race genetically superior via their own efforts"
msgstr ""
"老实说，阿尔加诺伊德族主要想将其用作飞船的高品质燃料，以及开发更高效的定位技术来获取稀有贵重物品。万泽尔蒂姆族希望用它创造更耐用独特的建筑材料，通过注入BL9来改进现有科技与武器。\n"
"\n"
"    达夫拉尼德斯族渴望显著推进现有的突变与基因拼接研究，试图通过自身努力使种族在基因层面变得优越。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Printed Wanzeltium's Journal - What a Nice Opportunity"
msgid_plural "Printed Wanzeltium's Journal - What a Nice Opportunitys"
msgstr[0] "印刷版万泽尔蒂姆日志 - 多好的机会"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Printed Wanzeltium's Journal - What a Nice
#. Opportunity"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"Our civilization is one of the greatest examples of our race's pragmatism. We build magnificent structures, advanced technologies, weapons, armor based on inventions of our dedicated scientists and engineers. We must be proud, of our government, of us being superior to majority of other races, of us essentially monopolizing tech market in our and local galaxy systems.\n"
" \n"
"    Ways of conquering for us are via diplomacy, money, financial enslavements, dependency of others on us, this we use for our own advantage. Not really proud to work with a bunch of space pirates, Arganoides, neither with blood craving, killing for sport or whatever savages, Saldeniums. However, Davranides...are obsessed with their genetical splicing and deep science...we must not tread on them, be allies, but keep an eye on them obviously"
msgstr ""
"我们的文明是我们种族实用主义的最佳典范之一。我们基于专注的科学家与工程师的发明，建造宏伟建筑、先进科技、武器和护甲。我们应当感到自豪——为我们的政府，为我们优于大多数其他种族，为我们基本垄断了本星系及邻近星系系统的科技市场。\n"
"\n"
"    我们的征服之道在于外交、金钱、金融奴役、他族对我们的依赖，我们利用这些为自己谋利。与一群太空海盗——阿尔加诺伊德族合作并不光彩，与嗜血、为运动或随便什么理由杀戮的野蛮人——萨尔德尼姆族合作亦然。然而，达夫拉尼德斯族……痴迷于基因拼接与深奥科学……我们不应与他们为敌，可结为盟友，但显然需保持警惕。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Printed Wanzeltium's Journal - What Has Our Race Turned Into?"
msgid_plural "Printed Wanzeltium's Journal - What Has Our Race Turned Into?s"
msgstr[0] "印刷版万泽尔蒂姆日志 - 我们的种族变成了什么？"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Printed Wanzeltium's Journal - What Has Our Race
#. Turned Into?"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"We change as we advance. In terms of our technological advancements, no other race is match for us, but this turns us into cruel, devious, calculating tyrants slowly. We've monopolized tech markets successfully in our, also in local galaxy systems. We've grown proud of ourselves so much that conquered races are shunned upon by our native citizens, exploited by local companies as slaves.\n"
" \n"
"    This entire attempt to seize BL9 on a ravaged planet, killing everyone on sight including humans, proves my point. We've formed an 'Alliance' with 'adventurers' or pirates, Arganoides. We deal with violent wars waging warriors and mercenaries, Saldeniums. Though, Davranides are the most shady of them all. I've never seen a race so obsessed with genetical splicing or mutations, I've heard stories of how tyrannical their superiors are, 'directing' all of their citizens according to their own world view as well"
msgstr ""
"我们随着进步而改变。在技术发展方面，没有其他种族能与我们匹敌，但这使我们逐渐变成了残忍、狡诈、精于算计的暴君。我们成功垄断了我们所在星系以及本地星系群的技术市场。我们变得如此骄傲自大，以至于被征服的种族遭到我们本土公民的排斥，被当地公司当作奴隶剥削。\n"
"\n"
"    这次在满目疮痍的星球上夺取BL9、见人就杀（包括人类）的整个行动，恰恰证明了我的观点。我们与'冒险者'或海盗阿尔加诺伊德结成了'联盟'。我们与发动暴力战争的战士和雇佣兵萨尔代尼厄姆打交道。不过，达夫拉尼德是所有种族中最阴暗的。我从未见过如此痴迷于基因拼接或突变的种族，我听说过他们的上级是多么专制，按照自己的世界观'指导'所有公民。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Printed Davranide's Journal - With BL9 We Will Prevail"
msgid_plural "Printed Davranide's Journal - With BL9 We Will Prevails"
msgstr[0] "打印的达夫拉尼德日志 - 凭借BL9我们将获胜"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Printed Davranide's Journal - With BL9 We Will
#. Prevail"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"We all contribute to our society's advancing. Genetical splicing of microorganisms, creation of mutagens along with drugs based on their properties, lots of work on peculiar ones, such as symbiotes, we excel at all of this. Our society does it's best to 'direct' our own people to the right way, even if it means prohibitions or strict rules to abide by for our own citizens. Some fools even say, 'exploiting' or simply 'experimenting on' inferior races, it's for their own good, it's for our own society's good.\n"
" \n"
"    Our government, our diligently working scientists, researchers, subjects, all work for the sake of Davranides' future of all of us united with no traces of opposition between us. With BL9, a unique, flexible, powerful symbiote, we will be able to alter our own race genetically to be the dominant race across hundreds of galaxies. Calculating Wanzeltiums with other races all across galaxies depending on them will be our mere slaves when we use BL9 to advance our race as well"
msgstr ""
"我们都为我们社会的进步做出贡献。微生物的基因拼接、诱变剂以及基于其特性的药物研发、对共生体等特殊生物的大量研究，我们在所有这些方面都出类拔萃。我们的社会竭尽全力'引导'我们的人民走上正途，即使这意味着对我们的公民实施禁令或严格的规则。有些傻瓜甚至说，'剥削'或仅仅是'在'劣等种族身上'做实验'，是为了他们好，也是为了我们社会的好。\n"
"\n"
"    我们的政府、我们勤奋工作的科学家、研究人员、实验对象，所有人都在为达夫拉尼德的未来而努力，让我们所有人团结一致，没有一丝反对的痕迹。凭借BL9这种独特、灵活、强大的共生体，我们将能够从基因上改造我们的种族，成为跨越数百个星系的统治种族。精于算计的万泽尔蒂厄姆以及其他依赖他们的星系种族，当我们使用BL9来推进我们的种族时，他们都将成为我们的奴隶。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Printed Davranide's Journal - Escape from My Own Brethren"
msgid_plural "Printed Davranide's Journal - Escape from My Own Brethrens"
msgstr[0] "打印的达夫拉尼德日志 - 逃离我的同胞"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Printed Davranide's Journal - Escape from My Own
#. Brethren"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"I've grown without father, like majority of Davranides families. We breed or 'fuck', they feed us a drug that cleanses love, affection hormones, amplifying pleasure hormones. Simply no love or affection allowed, it confuses minds they say. A bright child, I've got education in a prestigious university, worked in one of our top symbiotes research centers. I've learned a lot from our female mentor, she has shown me her personal projects, hidden from authorities, beneficial drugs, not just symbiote weapons. One of them restores all of our hormones to normal levels. We've developed forbidden affection, love, got lost in it but we were happy.\n"
" \n"
"    One of our authorities suspects 'unsanctioned experiments', frames my mentor, she gets killed, my own people destroy all of trust I had for them. Years after, I'm an experienced scientist. This fucktard confronts me, tells me I should be grateful he didn't frame me. I tell him all I think about him. We fight, he forcefully injects me with an experimental symbiote. I brutally smash fuckard into a pulp with my tentacle hammers. I escape via 'Alliance' portal to Earth, then I disguise as a human, I try to help a friendly organization to rebuild. Search for love, tell 'fuck off' to everyone else who prevents you from doing so. Find him or her. Be happy. I still search for my love with hope as well"
msgstr ""
"我和大多数达夫拉尼德家庭一样，在没有父亲的环境中长大。我们繁殖或'交配'，他们给我们喂一种药物，清除爱情、情感激素，放大快感激素。根本不允许有爱或情感，他们说这会扰乱心智。作为一个聪明的孩子，我在一所名牌大学接受了教育，在我们顶级的共生体研究中心之一工作。我从我们的女导师那里学到了很多，她向我展示了她的个人项目，这些项目对当局保密，是有益的药物，不仅仅是共生体武器。其中一种药物能将我们所有的激素恢复到正常水平。我们发展出了被禁止的情感、爱情，深陷其中，但我们很快乐。\n"
"\n"
"    我们的一位当局者怀疑'未经批准的实验'，陷害了我的导师，她被杀死了，我自己的同胞摧毁了我对他们所有的信任。多年后，我成为了一名经验丰富的科学家。这个混蛋找到我，告诉我我应该感激他没有陷害我。我把我对他的所有想法都告诉了他。我们打了起来，他强行给我注射了一种实验性共生体。我用我的触手锤残忍地将这个混蛋砸成了肉酱。我通过'联盟'的传送门逃到了地球，然后伪装成人类，我试图帮助一个友好的组织进行重建。寻找爱，对任何阻止你这样做的人说'滚开'。找到他或她。要幸福。我仍然满怀希望地寻找我的爱。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Printed Davranide's Journal - Technologies that Can Save People"
msgid_plural ""
"Printed Davranide's Journal - Technologies that Can Save Peoples"
msgstr[0] "打印的达夫拉尼德日志 - 能够拯救人民的技术"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Printed Davranide's Journal - Technologies that
#. Can Save People"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"I honestly try to not hide valuable info from my colleagues, but only 3 people: Subject5, Ulysses, I know about this. Just can't trust everyone, I'm essentially an exile to my own race, yet also one of the alien invaders to humans. Wanzeltiums with me have developed a unique technology: Energy Shield Generators that create a gigantic energy field based on sources that we've found on our planets. This field can protect people from horrors of Cataclysm, keeping even 'Alliance' militia away, shields are this strong.\n"
" \n"
"    Luckily, I've contributed greatly to making blueprints, with me being responsible for most of this technology, they won't be able to replicate it any time soon. Still, version that I have built has been definitely brought to their main base here but they have no idea how to make it work. Not even mentioning need to salvage more of their tech to get more power cells to make multiple Shield Generators. If Ulysses' child, Subject5, is clever enough with putting intel or journals, armed survivors may help us to cleanse all of these locations so that Shield Generator can be safely retrieved. We lack military, we're trying to repel 'THEIR' attacks as much as we can, we clearly need help from survivors as well"
msgstr ""
"老实说，我尽量不向我的同事隐瞒有价值的信息，但只有三个人：实验体5号、尤利西斯，我知道这件事。只是不能信任所有人，我本质上是被自己种族流放的人，但对人类来说也是外星入侵者之一。和我在一起的万泽尔蒂厄姆开发了一项独特的技术：能量护盾发生器，它能基于我们在自己星球上发现的能源创造一个巨大的能量场。这个力场可以保护人们免受大灾变的恐怖，甚至能将'联盟'民兵挡在外面，护盾就是这么强大。\n"
"\n"
"    幸运的是，我在制作蓝图方面贡献很大，由于我对这项技术的大部分负责，他们短期内将无法复制它。不过，我建造的版本肯定已经被带到了他们在这里的主要基地，但他们不知道如何让它工作。更不用说需要打捞更多他们的技术来获得更多的能量电池，以制造多个护盾发生器。如果尤利西斯的孩子，实验体5号，足够聪明地放置情报或日志，武装幸存者可能会帮助我们清理所有这些地点，以便安全地取回护盾发生器。我们缺乏军事力量，我们正在尽力击退'他们'的攻击，我们显然也需要幸存者的帮助。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Printed Subject5's Journal - My Story"
msgid_plural "Printed Subject5's Journal - My Storys"
msgstr[0] "打印的实验体5号日志 - 我的故事"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Printed Subject5's Journal - My Story"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"I've grown in one of our organization's core centers.Mymy father is a bright very experienced symbiotes scientist, yet he's a very kind, humane person, he wants me to be a scientist. My mother is a former scientist who mutated into a very graceful plant humanoid, retaining most of her humanity. She abandoned us, because she feared of what our own people could do to our family for having a mutant as a member of our organization. Years after, I've essentially grown indifferent to my father's work.\n"
" \n"
"    'THEY' attacked our core center, our own leader betrayed all of us. Hundreds of our people killed, kidnapped, abducted. Hundreds of mutated soldiers, vile creatures with inhumane strength and agility. Some of us escaped, like my father with some scientists, workers and our main agent. I didn't follow them. I ran to labs, I've injected myself with one of experimental symbiotes, BL9, my father has been working on it for years. Managed to use my new abilities to escape safely, alone. I search for remnants of our organization, I know they exist, I know they along with my father have survived. With this intel, journals, survivors could help me, our organization to fight our enemies successfully hopefully as well"
msgstr ""
"我在我们组织的核心中心之一长大。我的父亲是一位聪明且经验丰富的共生体科学家，但他也是一个非常善良、人道的人，他希望我成为一名科学家。我的母亲是一位前科学家，她变异成了一个非常优雅的植物人形，保留了她大部分的人性。她抛弃了我们，因为她害怕我们的人会因为我们的组织里有一个突变体成员而对我们家做什么。多年后，我基本上对父亲的工作变得漠不关心。\n"
"\n"
"    '他们'袭击了我们的核心中心，我们自己的领袖背叛了我们所有人。我们数百人被杀害、绑架、劫持。数百名变异士兵，拥有非人力量和敏捷性的邪恶生物。我们中的一些人逃走了，比如我父亲和一些科学家、工人以及我们的主要特工。我没有跟着他们。我跑进实验室，给自己注射了一种实验性共生体BL9，我父亲已经研究它多年了。设法利用我的新能力安全逃脱，独自一人。我寻找我们组织的残余，我知道他们存在，我知道他们和我父亲一起幸存了下来。有了这些情报和日志，幸存者或许也能帮助我、我们的组织成功地对抗我们的敌人。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Printed Agent's Journal - Who I am"
msgid_plural "Printed Agent's Journal - Who I ams"
msgstr[0] "打印的特工日志 - 我是谁"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Printed Agent's Journal - Who I am"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"I am an agent working on one of the remnants of many secret organizations that existed before Cataclysm. I was born in one of it's main hidden facilities, my father was a retired military officer who was hired as a mercenary and worked long for this organization.\n"
" \n"
"    Obviously, such organizations had and many still have many hidden facilities, vaults, many different structures, an unbelievable amount of resources to feed and supply multiple generations' of survivors and it's agents' offspring.\n"
" \n"
"    For many years I've been training diligently to become not just a survivor and a scavenger - but an agent who can search and scavenge for rare resources as well along with the basic ones. However, our own leader betrayed us, selling us to 'THEM', hoping to be one of 'THEIR' allies in New World that 'THEY' want to build.\n"
" \n"
"    'THEY' have killed, abducted many of our people, but many of us have also managed to escape. We've made secret BL9 research, safety bases thanks to Ulysses along with many of our scientists who believe that we can modify it to be safe, beneficial even to use for equipment or even drugs. I try to do my best to strive if not for flourishment but at the very least continued existence along with survival of our organization, my people..."
msgstr ""
"我是一名特工，效力于大灾变前众多秘密组织中残存的一支。我出生在其一处主要隐藏设施内，父亲是退役军官，受雇为雇佣兵，长期为该组织工作。\n"
"\n"
"显然，这类组织过去拥有、且许多至今仍掌握着大量隐藏设施、避难所、各式建筑，以及难以置信的资源储备，足以供养和供应数代幸存者及其特工后代。\n"
"\n"
"多年来我刻苦训练，不仅为了成为幸存者和拾荒者——更要成为能搜寻基础及稀有资源的特工。然而，我们的首领背叛了我们，将我们出卖给“他们”，妄想成为“他们”欲建立的新世界中“他们”的盟友。\n"
"\n"
"“他们”杀害、绑架了我们许多人，但我们中也有不少成功逃脱。得益于尤利西斯和许多相信我们能将其改造为安全甚至有益于装备或药物使用的科学家，我们建立了秘密的BL9研究安全基地。我竭尽全力奋斗，不求兴盛，只求我们组织与我的人民能延续存在、幸存下去……"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"Printed Military Partners' Journal - Together Forever Against Bioweapons "
"Part 1"
msgid_plural ""
"Printed Military Partners' Journal - Together Forever Against Bioweapons "
"Part 1s"
msgstr[0] "印刷版军事搭档日志——永远并肩对抗生化武器 第一部分"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Printed Military Partners' Journal - Together
#. Forever Against Bioweapons Part 1"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"Alright, she let me write this first, because I suck at writing coherently, hah. Weird name for our journal, but I would not have even survived half of our encounters without her. Tough lady she is. Now to business. It was before Cataclysm. I thought we killed this bastard in his mansion, with us barely managing do this successfully. We were trying to acquire enough proof in order to close, as we later learned, his superiors' organization for good, standing behind incident in that mansion, but no.\n"
" \n"
"    In the same year, horrible incident in That City. Small city, in the middle of nowhere, perfect place to conduct experiments. Hidden laboratory, unsanctioned bioweapons experiments going wrong, population turning into aggressive mutants, city being nuked from the face of Earth essentially. Many evacuated, not witnessing anything, luckily for them. However, some were caught in the middle of these events: former police officer man with my engineer sister with a little girl, also my partner.\n"
" \n"
"    My partner, as a veteran military agent, was sent there to find essentially traces of whatever turned this many people into horrifying mutants or drugs that would counter this bioweapon. What she went through, what she found, what she saw in That City though was even more interesting. Diary of main scientist with proof of one of his samples being stolen from him by military men. Highly trained female infiltrator searching for something in laboratory. Giant fucktard mutated bioweapon that deliberately hunted down remaining survivors in That City, chased my partner, that she has managed to kill, luckily for us"
msgstr ""
"好吧，她让我先写这部分，因为我实在不擅长连贯写作，哈。这日志名字真怪，但要是没有她，我连一半遭遇都活不下来。她真是个硬核的女人。言归正传。那是在大灾变之前。我以为我们在他豪宅里干掉了那混蛋，当时我们勉强才成功。我们本想搜集足够证据来彻底端掉——后来才知道——他上级的组织，那个在豪宅事件背后撑腰的势力，但没能如愿。\n"
"\n"
"同年，那座城市发生了可怕事件。一座小城，地处偏僻，是做实验的完美地点。隐藏实验室，未经授权的生化武器实验出错，居民变成狂暴突变体，城市基本上被从地球上抹去了。许多人被疏散，幸运地没目睹任何事。但有些人被卷入了事件中心：一名前警察带着我工程师姐姐和一个小女孩，还有我的搭档。\n"
"\n"
"我的搭档作为资深军事特工，被派去搜寻任何能将这么多人变成恐怖突变体的痕迹，或是能对抗这种生化武器的药物。但她在那个城市的经历、发现和目睹的一切更加惊人。主要科学家的日记，里面有证据表明他的一个样本被军方人员偷走。训练有素的女渗透者在实验室里寻找某物。还有那个故意猎杀城市幸存者、追杀我搭档的巨型混蛋突变生化武器——幸好她成功干掉了它。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"Printed Military Partners' Journal - Together Forever Against Bioweapons "
"Part 2"
msgid_plural ""
"Printed Military Partners' Journal - Together Forever Against Bioweapons "
"Part 2s"
msgstr[0] "印刷版军事搭档日志——永远并肩对抗生化武器 第二部分"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Printed Military Partners' Journal - Together
#. Forever Against Bioweapons Part 2"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"Hmm, let's continue this. What a name for a journal, I like this soft side of his, hah. This man is essentially definition of reliability, formidability. Where do I continue? Aha, yes, That City events. Was I surprised that there was conspiracy involved? Not really. That scum we thought we had killed in that mansion was cunning, devious, just like that woman who changed God knows how many employers. Organization's founder, that was behind events of that mansion along with That City, was no less of a mad man. The more ambitious they were, the more fucked up their ideas were. Some wanted regional power, some wanted riches, some wanted world domination, whereas some were so fucked up in terms of their ideas that I'm glad we've killed them.\n"
" \n"
"   Him and his superiors had a simple plan. First, retrieve whatever of their horrible work they left there, then leave no witnesses thanks to their bio-soldiers hunters, then let government do their job of nuking city so that nobody would know of this. These bastards' arrogance, huh? No way, fuckers. Not only me with some good people have escaped safely, we have also managed to destroy a lot of these bio-soldiers with all of these hunters. I've acquired plenty of intel to learn that fucker from that mansion was alive, plotting to continue work of his superiors. He later killed them, betrayed everyone he knew.\n"
" \n"
"    I can tell you more, there were bioweapons with all kinds of private mutants armies in many parts of the world essentially. Private military organizations, rich, power craving people, cultists, all sorts of madmen. All tied to someone bigger than them. Then Cataclysm happened. Still, me, my partner with other agents have luckily managed to assemble our team again"
msgstr ""
"嗯，继续写吧。这日志名字真有意思，我喜欢他这柔软的一面，哈。这男人简直就是可靠与强悍的代名词。从哪儿接着说呢？啊对，那座城市的事件。我惊讶于其中有阴谋吗？并不。我们以为在豪宅干掉的那人渣狡猾又阴险，就像那个天知道换过多少雇主的女人一样。那个组织创始人，幕后策划了豪宅和城市事件的家伙，同样是个疯子。他们野心越大，想法就越扭曲。有人想要地区霸权，有人想要财富，有人想要统治世界，还有些人的想法变态到我很庆幸我们干掉了他们。\n"
"\n"
"他和他的上级有个简单计划：先回收他们遗留的恐怖成果，再用他们的生化士兵猎人灭口，最后让政府核平城市以掩盖一切。这些混蛋多傲慢啊？没门，狗杂种。不仅我和一些好人安全逃脱，我们还干掉了大量生化士兵和那些猎人。我搜集到足够情报，得知豪宅那混蛋还活着，图谋继续他上级的事业。他后来杀了他们，背叛了所有认识的人。\n"
"\n"
"我可以告诉你更多：世界各地都有生化武器和各类私人突变体军队。私人军事组织、贪婪的权贵、邪教徒、各种疯子。全都联系着某个更大的幕后黑手。然后大灾变发生了。但幸运的是，我、我的搭档和其他特工成功重新集结了队伍。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"Printed Military Partners' Journal - Together Forever Against Bioweapons "
"Part 3"
msgid_plural ""
"Printed Military Partners' Journal - Together Forever Against Bioweapons "
"Part 3s"
msgstr[0] "印刷版军事搭档日志——永远并肩对抗生化武器 第三部分"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Printed Military Partners' Journal - Together
#. Forever Against Bioweapons Part 3"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"Interesting, let's talk about our newly assembled team of former military agents. Clearly, Cataclysm happened, however, our training, our experience, our stubbornness really saved our asses. Each of involved agents had a safety plan, in case of global threat that would significantly damage or mostly destroy communications systems. Special safezones located across the entire world for agents from various countries. Back then, 4 of us were stationed in North America. This includes me, my partner, also my sister along with her police officer survivor, hah. They became a couple, their first 'survivors date' taught them how to care for each other real good.\n"
" \n"
"   My partner wants us to stay here, to help local survivor structures with more mundane stuff that requires more concentration. Clearing local areas, handling logistics, making safe routes, expanding survivors' structures, helping find safe sources of water. Forget about secret vile organizations, eh? That's what younger professionals are for, right? My sister with her police officer promoted to a government agent, so, leave this shit for them to investigate?\n"
" \n"
"    Maybe she is right, we need to care for each other, settle down together, help local survivors, ensure our own safety hopefully. We should also convince our couple of adventurers to do the same. Maybe not. No, not now. Cults, 'THEY', 'True Superiors', this fucker is still out there. Unless we get help from survivors. Maybe we have a chance to settle down, survive, live together hopefully as well"
msgstr ""
"有意思，来谈谈我们新集结的前军事特工小队。显然，大灾变发生了，但我们的训练、经验和固执真的救了我们的命。每个相关特工都有安全预案，以应对严重破坏通讯系统的全球性威胁。世界各地设有针对各国特工的特殊安全区。当时，我们四人驻扎在北美。包括我、我的搭档、我姐姐和她的警察幸存者，哈。他们成了一对，第一次“幸存者约会”就教会了他们如何好好照顾彼此。\n"
"\n"
"我的搭档希望我们留在这里，用更日常的事务帮助本地幸存者组织：清理区域、处理后勤、开辟安全路线、扩建幸存者设施、寻找安全水源。别管那些邪恶秘密组织了，嗯？那是年轻专业人士的事，对吧？我姐姐和她的警察男友升任政府特工了，所以把这些破事留给他们调查？\n"
"\n"
"也许她是对的，我们需要彼此照顾，安定下来，帮助本地幸存者，确保自身安全。我们也该说服那对冒险家情侣这么做。或许不。不，现在不行。邪教、“他们”、“真上峰”，那混蛋还在外面。除非我们得到幸存者帮助。也许我们有机会安定下来，幸存，共同生活。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"Printed Military Partners' Journal - Together Forever Against Bioweapons "
"Part 4"
msgid_plural ""
"Printed Military Partners' Journal - Together Forever Against Bioweapons "
"Part 4s"
msgstr[0] "印刷版军事搭档日志——永远并肩对抗生化武器 第四部分"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Printed Military Partners' Journal - Together
#. Forever Against Bioweapons Part 4"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"Aha, so he has some hopes to settle down with me, that's very sweet! That's beneficial for our own safety. All 4 of us should be thankful that we have even managed to survive, assemble our team again. With intel that we've learned about strange organizations' activities in New England, no doubt that bio-soldiers, mutants are again being produced by shady masterminds. The most prominent are Strange Cult, 'THEY', there are also rumors of a more discreet organization called 'True Superiors'. Considering how careful 'Alliance' is, sheer numbers of these bio-soldiers, all of this made aliens choose a safe option of allying with them.\n"
" \n"
"    Still, they are much weaker than pre-Cataclysm private military organizations, they are simply remnants of former ones. However, they are way too sophisticated for mere remnants. I know some altruistic remnants of organizations, they are quite advanced, but are still forced into hiding. They even rely on help from local survivors. I'm not sure if we should concentrate on restoring safety in our local areas like professional survivors, or support my partner's obsession with further investigating these ourselves, I'm confused honestly.\n"
" \n"
"    What I know from our allies is that survivors do fend off these bastards successfully, they even attack their structures. Even though my distrust towards these experiments is greatest compared to all of us, these scientists have shown me proof of saving survivors from dangers of The Blob, Mycus, Triffids. Clearly, BL9 is a symbiote, it's origin is not of regular bioweapons. Only because it is either easily modifiable BL9 or horrible mutations from The Blob from local water, BL9 has a potential to be safe option to protect everyone, but only provided that experiments are long-term, guarantee physical, mental safety of hosts hopefully as well"
msgstr ""
"啊哈，原来他希望能和我安定下来，真贴心！这对我们自身安全也有利。我们四人都该庆幸能幸存并重新集结。根据我们掌握的新英格兰地区神秘组织活动情报，毫无疑问又有阴暗主谋在生产生化士兵和突变体。最突出的是神秘邪教、“他们”，还有传闻中更隐秘的“真上峰”组织。考虑到“联盟”的小心谨慎和这些生化士兵的数量，外星人选择了与他们结盟的安全选项。\n"
"\n"
"不过，他们比大灾变前的私人军事组织弱得多，只是前者的残存势力。但作为残存者，他们又过于精密。我知道一些利他主义的组织残余，他们相当先进，但仍被迫隐藏。他们甚至依赖本地幸存者的帮助。我不确定该像专业幸存者一样专注于恢复本地安全，还是支持我搭档亲自深入调查的执念，说实话我很困惑。\n"
"\n"
"从盟友处得知，幸存者确实成功击退了这些混蛋，甚至攻击了他们的设施。尽管我对这些实验的不信任是我们中最强烈的，但这些科学家向我展示了BL9从团块、真菌、特里菲德手中拯救幸存者的证据。显然，BL9是共生体，其起源不同于常规生化武器。正因为它是易改造的BL9或本地水源中团块引发的恐怖突变，BL9有潜力成为保护所有人的安全选项——但前提是实验必须长期进行，并确保宿主的生理与心理安全。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Printed Adventurers Couple's Journal - Bonds of Love Part 1"
msgid_plural "Printed Adventurers Couple's Journal - Bonds of Love Part 1s"
msgstr[0] "印刷版冒险家情侣日志——爱的羁绊 第一部分"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Printed Adventurers Couple's Journal - Bonds of
#. Love Part 1"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"Name sounds like a cheap romance novel, but let's keep it like this for fun, as long as it makes both of us chuckle. How we've met? Ah, shit, reminds me of so much we've went through with her. Two desperate survivors in these horrible conditions stuck in a city full of terrors. Love was least of my priorities back then. I worked as a police officer in my home town. As I remember, this started with me receiving my promotion of a corporal under the condition that I would move to a nearby town. I needed money, so I agreed. It was That City, one of the most horrible pre-Cataclysm cases of unsanctioned bioweapons experiments.\n"
" \n"
"    I was about to start my first day as a newly promoted corporal. I was being late when I've heard the sirens all across the city, evacuation helicopters recklessly getting away. On my way to police station I saw people aggressively chasing other people, leaping at them, grabbing them by their legs. They clawed them savagely then started to eat their flesh. It was horrifying and disgusting, I puked upon seeing this right in my car. Some of them saw me and ran towards my car, I pressed gas, running few of them over. I made my way to one of the closest relatively big markets.\n"
" \n"
"    I went to this market get supplies, also to possibly find a good melee weapon, a fire axe or a wrench. I heard a running noise from the outside towards the same door I entered. A girl armed with a revolver clumsily yet quickly entered with a shambler behind her. I aimed at it, telling her to get down. With a headshot I killed it. Then we both ran towards my car, quickly made our way out of there. She was a junior robotics engineering student in That City. Her brother was a high-ranking veteran policeman. This explained to me her being pretty good with guns"
msgstr ""
"这名字听起来像本廉价爱情小说，但为了好玩咱们就这么留着吧，只要能让咱俩都乐一乐就行。我们怎么相遇的？啊该死，这让我想起和她经历过的种种。两个绝望的幸存者，在这恐怖遍布的城市里，受困于恶劣环境。那时爱情根本排不上我的优先清单。我在家乡当过警察。记得事情始于我获得晋升为下士的机会，条件是调往邻近城镇。我需要钱，所以答应了。就是那座城市——大灾变前最骇人听闻的非法生物武器实验案例之一。\n"
"\n"
"    我正要开始晋升下士后的首个工作日。迟到途中，听见全城警报嘶鸣，撤离直升机不顾一切地逃离。去警局的路上，我看见人们疯狂追逐他人，扑上去抓住他们的腿。他们野蛮地撕扯，然后开始啃食血肉。这景象恐怖又恶心，我在车里直接吐了。其中几个发现我，冲向我的车，我猛踩油门碾过了几个。我设法逃到最近的一家较大超市。\n"
"\n"
"    我进超市寻找补给，也想找件趁手的近战武器，比如消防斧或扳手。突然听见门外传来奔跑声，正朝我进来的方向。一个女孩笨拙却迅速地冲进来，手里攥着左轮手枪，身后跟着个蹒跚的怪物。我举枪瞄准，喊她趴下。一记爆头解决了它。随后我们一同跑向我的车，火速逃离了那里。她是那座城市的机器人工程专业大三学生。她哥哥是资深高阶警官。这解释了她为何枪法相当不错。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Printed Adventurers Couple's Journal - Bonds of Love Part 2"
msgid_plural "Printed Adventurers Couple's Journal - Bonds of Love Part 2s"
msgstr[0] "印刷版冒险者情侣日记 - 爱的羁绊 第2部分"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Printed Adventurers Couple's Journal - Bonds of
#. Love Part 2"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"This really is a cheap romance novel name! Though, I actually find it funny. I was getting a robotics engineering degree in my university. I always found applied math, physics pretty fun. My brother, the cop in our family, approved of my decision, he is all fists and fighting, so analytical one in our family is a must. As my dear says about his first day of corporal rank experience, I felt the same way back then. Love, no. Safety, protection, yes. That's how I felt back then. My brother was missing, I was alone on the streets, searching for him, when the whole city went to shit. I ran as fast as I could to nearest building, coming across him. A guy in a police uniform, aiming his gun at me, telling me to get down. So I did, out of fear, yet he killed a shambler behind me.\n"
" \n"
"    We made our way in his car to police station, which, disappointingly, was also infested with these mutants. Most were shamblers, but there was this horrible type. A fleshy beast with a grotesque head, long tongue, no eyes, and long claws size of a human. We were chased by a giant brute in this building. As we were hiding from it, I found documents proving that my brother left That City weeks ago to do his private investigation. Also we found a secret underground passage in That City's police station. It was leading to some kind of a laboratory complex, which answered most of our questions in terms of what the heck even happened in That City.\n"
" \n"
"    This entire lab was a huge conspiracy. Unsanctioned bioweapons experiments. An incident with bioweapon leak was a result of lab's main mutated scientist going mad over his secret creation being stolen by some private military. On our way out of lab, we saved this scientist's daughter. Three of us barely made it out of there safely via an underground train system with that scientist beast and a huge brute chasing us"
msgstr ""
"这名字确实像廉价爱情小说！不过，我其实觉得挺有趣。当时我在大学攻读机器人工程学位。我一直觉得应用数学和物理很有意思。我哥哥——家里的警察——支持我的决定，他是个拳脚派，所以家里必须有个分析型人才。就像我亲爱的描述他晋升下士首日的经历那样，我当时的感受也差不多。爱情？不。安全、保护？是的。那就是我当时的想法。哥哥失踪了，我独自在街头寻找他，整座城市却突然陷入混乱。我拼命跑向最近的建筑，正好遇见他。一个穿警服的男人用枪指着我，命令我趴下。我照做了——出于恐惧——但他击毙了我身后的蹒跚者。\n"
"\n"
"    我们乘他的车前往警局，可惜那里也充斥着变异体。大部分是蹒跚者，但有种特别可怕的类型：血肉模糊的巨兽，顶着怪诞的脑袋，长舌无眼，爪子比人还长。在这栋建筑里，我们被一个巨型蛮兵追赶。躲藏时，我发现了证明哥哥数周前已离城进行私人调查的文件。我们还在那座城市警局里找到一条秘密地下通道。它通向某种实验室建筑群，解答了我们对城市异变的多数疑问。\n"
"\n"
"    整个实验室就是个巨大阴谋。未经授权的生物武器实验。一次生物武器泄漏事件，起因是实验室首席变异科学家因自己的秘密造物被某私人军事公司窃取而发狂。离开实验室途中，我们救下了这位科学家的女儿。我们三人勉强通过地下铁路系统安全逃脱，那只科学家变异的怪物和巨型蛮兵一直在身后追赶。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Printed Adventurers Couple's Journal - Bonds of Love Part 3"
msgid_plural "Printed Adventurers Couple's Journal - Bonds of Love Part 3s"
msgstr[0] "印刷版冒险者情侣日记 - 爱的羁绊 第3部分"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Printed Adventurers Couple's Journal - Bonds of
#. Love Part 3"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"She is right, my honey really managed to rescue that scientist's daughter. Strange child, immune to That City's bioweapons, as she stated herself. That's what her father told her when injecting her with all kinds of shit. Her bruises were healing up at an extreme rate. The whole shit was really a conspiracy with shady people involved. This is what government told me later on. Hunter brute, horribly mutated scientist, stolen samples of bioweapons, shady female spy. That spy really did save my life multiple times, helping me to destroy this brute, but she clearly had her own motives there. Every time our paths crossed, I always knew that she had some errands to do, provided by her new employers. Whatever, we made it safe, now about events after That City essentially.\n"
" \n"
"    Let's just say that government has become interested in two barely trained survivors going through so much shit successfully. We've been 'offered' government agents jobs. Not much choice, considering what we've seen. Then these were times of my duty in various parts of the world. Strangely, current New England prominent factions of madmen that are obsessed with BL9 symbiote really remind me of what I've seen in Europe. Is that some kind of a bullshit trend? As years went by, I tried to convince my engineer girl to let me talk government out of her further involvement. I've been seeing more and more shit that I didn't get killed for only because I'm too useful to kill essentially.\n"
" \n"
"    Honey is too stubborn, she wanted to delve even deeper into this. Saving people from madmen with bioweapons is more important than building complex electromechanical systems. That's what she says. When Cataclysm happened, this tight grip was gone. So now we hunt for remnants of these madmen, whereas her brother with his partner try to rebuild everything in local areas. It's a fucking mess, but at least we've got each other to survive hopefully as well"
msgstr ""
"她说得对，我的甜心确实救下了那位科学家的女儿。古怪的孩子，据她自称对那座城市的生物武器免疫。这是她父亲给她注射各种乱七八糟东西时告诉她的。她的伤口以惊人速度愈合。整件事都是场阴谋，牵扯着见不得光的人。这是政府后来告诉我的。猎人蛮兵、严重变异的科学家、被盗的生物武器样本、神秘的女间谍。那个间谍确实多次救了我的命，帮我摧毁了这个蛮兵，但她显然另有动机。每次我们相遇，我都知道她带着新雇主交代的任务。无论如何，我们安全脱身了，现在说说那座城市之后的事吧。\n"
"\n"
"    这么说吧，政府对两个训练不足却成功经历这么多破事的幸存者产生了兴趣。我们被'提供'了政府特工的工作。考虑到我们的所见所闻，选择不多。之后便是我在世界各地执行任务的时期。奇怪的是，现在新英格兰地区那些痴迷BL9共生体的狂热派系，总让我想起在欧洲的见闻。这难道是某种狗屁潮流？年复一年，我试图说服我的工程师姑娘，让我去游说政府别再让她深入参与。我目睹了越来越多肮脏事，之所以没被灭口，纯粹是因为我太有利用价值。\n"
"\n"
"    甜心太固执，她甚至想更深入其中。她说：从生物武器狂人手中拯救民众，比构建复杂机电系统更重要。大灾变发生时，这种严密控制消失了。所以现在我们追猎这些狂人的残余势力，而她哥哥和搭档则试图重建当地秩序。真他妈一团糟，但至少我们还能彼此依靠，希望能一起活下去。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Printed Adventurers Couple's Journal - Bonds of Love Part 4"
msgid_plural "Printed Adventurers Couple's Journal - Bonds of Love Part 4s"
msgstr[0] "印刷版冒险者情侣日记 - 爱的羁绊 第4部分"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Printed Adventurers Couple's Journal - Bonds of
#. Love Part 4"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"My dear describes my motives pretty clearly. We've survived a horrifying incident in That City full of shady bastards behind it essentially. We've travelled across the world, fought madmen along with their creations. My dear warned me though that eventually we can uncover things that will make government treat us differently. I convinced him though that our usefulness simply matters much more to them than our knowledge, as long as we have no objections to working for them. Then Cataclysm happened. Governments were gone. No united control. Only individual organizations remained. Some new, some remnants of former organizations. All have different motives.\n"
" \n"
"    Even though there is a lot of work we have in terms of rebuilding everything, I've convinced my dear for us to become hunters of some sorts. We investigate activities of strange local cults, military formations. If we suspect them to have not particularly friendly motives, we carefully check their structures. Usually they clearly are hostile, attack everyone on sight, however some really are altruistic. Latter are much more discreet, not because it is their intention. They achieve their goals only by communicating with, helping people. They are forced into hiding, especially in New England area because of Strange Cults, 'THEM', 'True Superiors', 'Alliance'. Should not we help them to fend them off to keep everyone safe?\n"
" \n"
"    They all diligently hunt for BL9, all of these bastards. Even altruistic organizations that we've contacted convince us of BL9 not being a bioweapon, huh? I mean, pretty much everything around, The Blob, Mycus, Triffids, can be considered bioweapons, pretty much not safe for majority of people. BL9, as our allies state, can be modified, to be used as protection against other hostile microorganisms, they even have proof of this. I don't know, my brother would not agree, but if there are no alternative options. This potentially can be used as means to protect all of us, our offspring, hopefully as well"
msgstr ""
"我亲爱的把我的动机说得很清楚。我们在一座充满幕后黑手的城市里熬过了恐怖事件。我们走遍世界，与狂人及其造物作战。虽然亲爱的警告过我，最终我们可能发现会让政府改变对待方式的事情。但我让他相信：只要我们不反对为他们工作，我们的利用价值远比我们知道的事情更重要。然后大灾变发生了。政府瓦解了。没有统一控制。只剩下个别组织。有些是新的，有些是前组织的残余。各自动机不同。\n"
"\n"
"    尽管重建工作千头万绪，我还是说服了亲爱的，让我们成为某种猎人。我们调查当地诡异教派和军事组织的活动。若怀疑他们动机不纯，就仔细探查其架构。通常他们明显怀有敌意，见人就攻击，但确实有些组织是利他的。后者更为隐蔽——并非本意如此。他们只能通过沟通和帮助民众来实现目标。他们被迫隐藏，尤其在新英格兰地区，因为那些诡异教派、'他们'、'真圣会'、'联盟'的存在。我们难道不该帮他们抵御这些威胁，保护大家安全吗？\n"
"\n"
"    所有这些混蛋都在拼命搜寻BL9。就连我们接触过的利他组织也坚称BL9不是生物武器，嗯？我是说，周围几乎所有东西——吞噬之种、真菌族、三裂草——都能算生物武器，对多数人都不安全。但据盟友所说，BL9可以被改造，用作抵御其他有害微生物的防护，他们甚至有证据。我不知道，我哥哥肯定不会同意，但如果没有其他选择...这或许能成为保护我们所有人、我们后代的潜在手段，希望如此。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"Printed 'True Superiors' Leader's Journal - Evolution of The Worthy Part 1"
msgid_plural ""
"Printed 'True Superiors' Leader's Journal - Evolution of The Worthy Part 1s"
msgstr[0] "印刷版'真圣会'首领日记 - 适者进化 第1部分"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Printed 'True Superiors' Leader's Journal -
#. Evolution of The Worthy Part 1"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"Inventions of 20th century - can you imagine how impactful they were? Some have improved our lifestyle, others have advanced all of us as a civilization. But humans still remained filthy humans with their animal needs, failing to see the bigger picture of what humans are truly capable of. However, one particular discovery, that later led to an invention, gave some a chance to evolve from this filthy state of animals. I was one of such who was worthy of this evolution. I started to see the bigger picture. I obediently followed my benefactors, learned from them, made temporary friends, who proved to be incredibly useful in terms of knowledge they shared in field of bioweapons research.\n"
" \n"
"    Even though our organization made a lot of progress, that was not without curious feeble beings, limited by ethics, shoving their noses into what was beyond their comprehension. Not being a public figure in our organization, I was sent as a double agent to police department that was responsible for investigations related to one of our properties. Plan was simple, lure them into a trap in one of our mansions they intended to investigate. That plan failed, though, it was not mine in first place. When our weaker subjects failed to kill these two fuckers, I've decided to take on them myself, obviously, with help of one of our sophisticated creations. That failed, fuckers proved to be too stubborn, however, experience is what I've gained from this.\n"
" \n"
"    This failure brought a lot of unwanted attention to our organization. It needed to be restructured. So it was. My temporary friend, main scientist in our lab of That City, was given an order to accelerate development of new bioweapon. However, his views started to change. There were disagreements with his superiors. His own pride and foolishness gave me an advantage. Seeing my high intelligence, knowledge that I've gained from this 'friend' of mine, I've managed to convince my benefactor to forcefully acquire samples of newest bioweapon that my 'friend' has made in That City"
msgstr ""
"二十世纪的发明——你能想象它们的影响吗？有些改善了生活，有些推动了文明进步。但人类仍是肮脏的人类，带着动物般的需求，无法看清人类真正潜能的宏大图景。然而，一项特殊的发现（后来催生了发明）给了某些人从这种动物性肮脏状态进化的机会。我是获得这种进化资格的适格者。我开始看见更宏大的图景。我顺从地追随我的恩主，向他们学习，结交临时盟友——这些盟友在生物武器研究领域的知识分享方面被证明极具价值。\n"
"\n"
"    尽管我们组织取得长足进展，但总有好奇的弱者被伦理束缚，将鼻子伸向他们无法理解的事物。作为组织的非公开人物，我被派往负责调查我们某处资产的警局当双面间谍。计划很简单：诱使他们进入我们打算调查的宅邸陷阱。但这计划失败了——本来也不是我的主意。当我们较弱的实验体没能干掉那两个混蛋时，我决定亲自出手（当然带着我们精密造物的协助）。还是失败了，混蛋们太顽固，不过我也从中获得了经验。\n"
"\n"
"    这次失败给组织招来太多不必要的关注。需要重组。于是就这么做了。我的临时盟友——那座城市实验室的首席科学家——接到加速开发新型生物武器的命令。但他的观念开始改变。与上级产生分歧。他的自负和愚蠢给了我可乘之机。凭借我的高智商和从这位'朋友'处获得的知识，我说服恩主强行夺取了'朋友'在那座城市研制的最新生物武器样本。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"Printed 'True Superiors' Leader's Journal - Evolution of The Worthy Part 2"
msgid_plural ""
"Printed 'True Superiors' Leader's Journal - Evolution of The Worthy Part 2s"
msgstr[0] "印刷版'真圣会'首领日记 - 适者进化 第2部分"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Printed 'True Superiors' Leader's Journal -
#. Evolution of The Worthy Part 2"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"One of our top scientists, the one who taught me everything I knew back then about microorganisms research, became a liability, to my own advantage. Old fool didn't know that I was already working on my own organization. I sent a professional female spy to ambush our men and steal samples of that bioweapon. Fucking snake in red dress failed though. Luckily, she found more samples in that laboratory in addition to valuable intelligence from my former 'friend' that even that old fool didn't get his hands on. That City incident was a good reason for me to leave our organization under the pretext of being worried of further investigations. I had plenty of data to research until discovery in Europe.\n"
" \n"
"    Villagers, Cultists, Military, all turned into obedient mutants. This was somewhere in Europe. Controlled by some ambitious fucker. His research was really of high quality though, but not as good as what I've made with a later discovery. Didn't gain much from this except for being more careful with choosing people to work for me. That fucking snake in red dress fooled me, sent me a fake sample instead of a real one, never trust devious fuckers. I had temporary success with my latest discovery back then. It was perfect for global evolution according to my own views. I was enhanced like never before. I came as a guest to my former benefactor. I showed him everything that I've become, something that he could never possibly achieve, then I killed him.\n"
" \n"
"    Fuckers from that mansion ruined everything. My newest invention was entirely destroyed with me being forced into hiding. Until Cataclysm happened. The Blob, Mycus, Triffids, so much to research! However, none of them are even as near as sophisticated as alien symbiote, BL9, which is hunted even by alien pillagers from other galaxies. I have created 'True Superiors' organization, I have built 'THEIR' army, I have fooled 'Alliance', forcing them to work with my organization. These feeble altruistic fuckers think they can stop our evolution with a bunch of survivors?"
msgstr ""
"我们的一位顶尖科学家——那位曾教会我所有微生物研究知识的人——成了我的累赘，而这对我有利。那个老傻瓜不知道我早已在筹建自己的组织。我派了一名专业女间谍去伏击我们的人，窃取那种生物武器的样本。可惜那个穿红裙的婊子搞砸了。幸运的是，她在那个实验室里找到了更多样本，还从我那位前“朋友”那里获得了连那个老傻瓜都没弄到手的重要情报。那座城市的事件给了我一个绝佳借口，以担心进一步调查为由离开了我们的组织。我有大量数据可供研究，直到在欧洲被发现。\n"
"\n"
"村民、邪教徒、军人，全都变成了顺从的突变体。这发生在欧洲某地。被某个野心勃勃的混蛋控制着。不过他的研究质量确实很高，但还不如我后来基于一项发现所取得的成果。除了让我更谨慎地选择为我效力的人之外，这次经历没给我带来多少好处。那个穿红裙的婊子骗了我，给了我假样本而不是真货——永远别相信狡猾的混蛋。那时我基于最新发现取得了短暂的成功。按照我的观点，这对全球进化来说是完美的。我得到了前所未有的强化。我以客人身份拜访了我以前的恩人。我向他展示了我所成为的一切——他永远无法企及的东西，然后杀了他。\n"
"\n"
"那座宅邸的混蛋们毁了一切。我的最新发明被彻底摧毁，我被迫躲藏起来。直到大灾变发生。黏液怪、真菌怪、三脚怪，有太多东西可以研究了！然而，它们都没有外星共生体BL9那样精密复杂，甚至连来自其他星系的外星掠夺者都在猎捕它。我创建了“真·至高者”组织，我建立了“他们”的军队，我愚弄了“联盟”，迫使他们与我的组织合作。这些软弱的利他主义混蛋以为靠一群幸存者就能阻止我们的进化？"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"Printed Female Mercenary Spy's Journal - Fighting Thinking in Absolutes With"
" Espionage Part 1"
msgid_plural ""
"Printed Female Mercenary Spy's Journal - Fighting Thinking in Absolutes With"
" Espionage Part 1s"
msgstr[0] "印刷版女佣兵间谍日记——用间谍手段对抗绝对化思维 第一部分"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Printed Female Mercenary Spy's Journal -
#. Fighting Thinking in Absolutes With Espionage Part 1"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"My father taught me one very important thing when I was a young girl. He told me that it is wrong to think in absolutes. Has he done something significant in his life with this way of thinking? Maybe. Maybe not. What I know is that his advice greatly helps me in my work. My work is not just means of acquiring money. It helps me to prevent people who think in absolutes from shaping the world in a way that they like. This is especially important if we are talking about genetical experiments related to unknown microorganisms which have many uses. From healthy drugs, protection, extending lives of people to bioweapons. Don't ask me how I got in this field of work. Let's just say that I have received plenty of military experience to work as a professional mercenary spy.\n"
" \n"
"    I've heard of reputation of organization behind incidents in that mansion along with That City. No doubt that extremists were among it's leaders, intending to work on advanced bioweapons research. I was offered a job by an unknown man, who described himself as a former research scientist in that organization, who had changed his ways. My job was to intercept military, sent by that organization to kill their main scientist, stationed in That City's laboratory. My goal was not to save that scientist. Like I was told, scum simply wanted to sell property of their organization to highest bidder essentially. My task was to steal this property from military then bring it to my employer.\n"
" \n"
"    As a careful person I am, I waited for a perfect opportunity to ambush them. However, my stealth approach was interrupted by hordes of mutants, attacking both me along with military. The whole city went to shit within a few minutes. I had to run for my life essentially. However, I am a quite intelligent girl. I knew that lab must have contained various intelligence, notes, diaries, maybe even something more important. This scientist devoted himself to his work entirely. There must have been another sample in that laboratory. I managed to find both, though, it was very difficult to do based on what I've seen there honestly"
msgstr ""
"在我还是个小女孩时，父亲教给我一件非常重要的事。他告诉我，绝对化的思考方式是错误的。他凭借这种思维方式在生活中取得过重大成就吗？也许有，也许没有。我所知道的是，他的建议对我的工作帮助极大。我的工作不仅仅是赚钱的手段。它帮助我阻止那些思维绝对化的人按照他们喜欢的方式塑造世界。当我们谈论涉及未知微生物的基因实验时，这一点尤为重要——这些微生物用途广泛，从健康药物、防护措施、延长人类寿命到生物武器。别问我怎么进入这个领域的。只能说，我积累了丰富的军事经验，足以成为一名专业的佣兵间谍。\n"
"\n"
"我听说过那座宅邸和那座城市事件背后组织的名声。毫无疑问，其领导者中有极端分子，意图进行先进的生物武器研究。一个陌生男子给了我一份工作，他自称是该组织的前研究科学家，现已改过自新。我的任务是拦截该组织派去刺杀他们驻那座城市实验室首席科学家的军队。我的目标不是拯救那位科学家。正如我所知，那个人渣只是想把他们组织的财产卖给出价最高者。我的任务是从军队手中窃取这份财产，然后交给我的雇主。\n"
"\n"
"作为一个谨慎的人，我等待伏击他们的完美时机。然而，我的潜行被成群的突变体打断，它们同时攻击了我和军队。整座城市在几分钟内就陷入混乱。我基本上只能逃命。不过，我是个相当聪明的女孩。我知道实验室里一定藏有各种情报、笔记、日记，甚至可能还有更重要的东西。这位科学家完全投身于工作。那个实验室里肯定还有另一份样本。我设法找到了两者，尽管说实话，根据我在那里的所见，这非常困难。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"Printed Female Mercenary Spy's Journal - Fighting Thinking in Absolutes With"
" Espionage Part 2"
msgid_plural ""
"Printed Female Mercenary Spy's Journal - Fighting Thinking in Absolutes With"
" Espionage Part 2s"
msgstr[0] "印刷版女佣兵间谍日记——用间谍手段对抗绝对化思维 第二部分"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Printed Female Mercenary Spy's Journal -
#. Fighting Thinking in Absolutes With Espionage Part 2"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"Essentially in my work thinking in absolutes means either of two things. Either granting access to all of these drugs, genetically modified microorganisms, to general public. Giving them all for free. Not thinking that this can produce riots, forced acceleration of production. At the same time, similar inadequate total access can make available production of bioweapons for madmen. Both are extremists points of views that must be avoided. This is what gave me motivation when I was going through that ruined city. I trusted this man. He seemed like he was hating himself for his involvement in this mess. All he needed, he said, was to make sure that their property won't get into their hands. Incident in that mansion fooled me into trusting him.\n"
" \n"
"    I've found very important intelligence in police station, records of a former member of investigation department that almost got investigators' team killed in that mansion. It was said that man was incredibly devious, cunning. It's as if his betrayal was planned in advance. Whoever wrote this had suspicions of involvement of this organization in an attempted murder of investigators' team. This made me think of who I actually work for. However, there was no real proof of whether it was the same person or not. In the same police station I've met a newly promoted corporal, pretty young, seemed to lack experience, still, confident in a non-arrogant way, determined to survive, also escape to safety with whatever companion of his that he mentioned.\n"
" \n"
"    I saved his ass from one of hunters bioweapons sent to kill any witnesses. Hah, he was keep asking me questions. I tried to buzz him off saying that he should be glad that not only I didn't kill him, but also saved his ass multiple times as well. I didn't know that we would meet in Europe with him again. Well, I did steal a sample from him. Still, I knew by then who I worked for, sending him fake sample as a reward. What do I do now after Cataclysm? Well, I've recently brought an advanced BL9 sample to human disguised exiled alien scientist that helps humans survive"
msgstr ""
"在我的工作中，绝对化思维本质上意味着两件事之一：要么向公众开放所有这些药物、转基因微生物，免费提供一切，不考虑这可能导致骚乱、被迫加速生产；同时，类似的不加限制的全面开放也可能让疯子得以生产生物武器。两者都是必须避免的极端主义观点。这就是当我穿过那座废墟城市时的动力来源。我相信了这个男人。他似乎为自己卷入这场混乱而憎恨自己。他说，他只需要确保他们的财产不会落入他们手中。那座宅邸的事件让我误信了他。\n"
"\n"
"我在警察局发现了非常重要的情报：一份前调查部门成员的记录，他差点让调查小组在那座宅邸丧命。据说此人极其狡猾、诡计多端，仿佛他的背叛是预先策划的。记录者怀疑该组织涉嫌企图谋杀调查小组。这让我开始思考我究竟在为谁工作。然而，没有确凿证据证明是否是同一个人。在同一警察局，我遇到了一位新晋升的下士，相当年轻，似乎缺乏经验，但自信而不傲慢，决心生存下去，并与他提到的同伴一起逃往安全地带。\n"
"\n"
"我从一种被派来灭口的猎人生物武器手中救了他。哈，他不停地问我问题。我试图打发他走，说他不该庆幸我没杀他，还多次救了他的命吗？我不知道我们后来会在欧洲再次相遇。好吧，我确实从他那里偷了一份样本。但那时我已经知道我为谁工作，所以寄给他一份假样本作为回报。大灾变后我现在做什么？嗯，我最近把一个先进的BL9样本带给了一位伪装成人类、帮助人类生存的流亡外星科学家。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Printed Davranide's Journal - Super Soldier Project"
msgid_plural "Printed Davranide's Journal - Super Soldier Projects"
msgstr[0] "印刷版达夫拉尼德日记——超级士兵计划"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Printed Davranide's Journal - Super Soldier
#. Project"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"Usually we are not interested in projects of these savages. Majority of them are either mindless mutants, used for killing, or power hungry fools, obsessed with domination of local areas. They don't even care about improving living conditions for their own people. However, there are a few human scientists, who have told me about their most experienced scientist. It is the leader of 'True Superiors' organization at the same time essentially. Humans are feeble, mostly are worthless. But not this man. Even I, representative of a superior race, fear this man. It's like he is not even a man at this point. So what they said is that on their Militarized Island, with instructions made by this man, they developed a Super Soldier.\n"
" \n"
"    I came to Militarized Island to see quality of their work. It was pretty good, still, lacking many features that we could add. It was obviously a carefully made humanoid amalgamation of mutated animals that each of our 'Alliance' races brought here. Later when I wanted to talk with these scientists about our own, Davranides' projects, they told me that this man knows that I was one of the few Davranides scientists who showed interest in Super Soldier Project. Scientists said that this man insists that we enhance this project further. I said that I am not sure, but scientists simply replied. They said that Davranides will take on this work if 'Alliance' as a whole values their safety on Earth essentially. We don't want to make enemies out of our allies. We continued this project ourselves. Enhanced versions can be found in various impact sites Cave Systems, whereas experimental enhanced versions can be found in our own Mobile Bases"
msgstr ""
"通常我们对这些野蛮人的计划不感兴趣。他们大多要么是无脑的突变体，用于杀戮；要么是权欲熏心的傻瓜，痴迷于统治局部地区。他们甚至不关心改善自己人民的生活条件。然而，有几位人类科学家向我提过他们经验最丰富的科学家。此人本质上同时也是“真·至高者”组织的领袖。人类是软弱的，大多毫无价值。但这个人例外。即使是我——一个优越种族的代表——也畏惧此人。他仿佛此刻已非人类。据他们说，在他们的军事化岛屿上，按照此人的指示，他们开发出了一名超级士兵。\n"
"\n"
"我来到军事化岛屿考察他们的工作质量。相当不错，但仍缺乏许多我们能添加的特性。这显然是一个精心制作的人形融合体，由我们“联盟”各个种族带来的突变动物组合而成。后来当我想与这些科学家讨论我们达夫拉尼德人自己的项目时，他们告诉我，此人知道我是少数对超级士兵计划感兴趣的达夫拉尼德科学家之一。科学家们说，此人坚持要求我们进一步强化这个项目。我说我不确定，但科学家们只是回答：如果“联盟”整体重视他们在地球上的安全，达夫拉尼德人将接手这项工作。我们不想与盟友为敌。我们自己继续了这个项目。强化版本可以在各种撞击坑洞穴系统中找到，而实验性强化版本则在我们自己的移动基地里。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Printed Agent's Journal - Welcome to BL9 Safety Base"
msgid_plural "Printed Agent's Journal - Welcome to BL9 Safety Bases"
msgstr[0] "印刷版特工日记——欢迎来到BL9安全基地"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Printed Agent's Journal - Welcome to BL9 Safety
#. Base"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"You have either managed to find or return to any of BL9 Safety Bases, it is good that you are here, safe! Proceed to Control Sector to talk to Base Android, responsible for safe work of all systems in this particular BL9 Safety Base. You can talk to Base Android to ask her various questions. She has a built-in system which makes her able to read various intel along with journals which we have collected. They are all optional to read, but are advised to read in general. They are all categorized, which only means that she will read them, based on your choices of questions categories along with your questions in general. You can go to Leisure Center to get a beverage or a drink from there. You might wonder why here there is nobody of our organization's representatives? Answer is simple. Safety. You probably understand that we are aware of all kinds of inhabitants roaming around. This includes benevolent survivors, hopefully, you are one of these survivors. At the same time these can be bandits, murderers, maniacs, double agents of Strange Cult, 'THEM', 'True Superiors', 'Alliance' obviously. We prefer not to give any chance to either of these horrible bastards to try to weaken or damage our organization.\n"
" \n"
"    The most important journal for you to read is 'Instructions for Survivors' which is a must for survival of survivors who are interested in helping our organization achieve it's goal types which we concentrate on for survival of humanity in general. Key goal of our organization is to bring hope, safety, civilization that will guarantee survival, possibility of procreation to survivors hopefully as well"
msgstr ""
"你设法找到或返回了某个BL9安全基地，很高兴你在这里，安全！请前往控制区与基地安卓交谈，她负责这个特定BL9安全基地所有系统的安全工作。你可以与基地安卓交谈，向她提出各种问题。她内置了一套系统，使她能够阅读我们收集的各种情报和日记。这些都可以选择性地阅读，但一般建议阅读。它们都已分类，这意味着她将根据你选择的问题类别以及你的具体问题来读取相关内容。你可以去休闲中心喝点饮料。你可能会奇怪为什么这里没有我们组织的代表？答案很简单：安全。你可能明白，我们知道各种居民在四处游荡。这包括善意的幸存者——希望你是其中之一。同时，也可能是强盗、杀人犯、疯子、诡异教派的双重间谍，以及“他们”、“真·至高者”、“联盟”的成员。我们宁愿不给这些可怕的混蛋任何试图削弱或损害我们组织的机会。\n"
"\n"
"对你来说，最重要的日记是《幸存者指南》，这对于有兴趣帮助我们组织实现其目标类型的幸存者来说是必读的——我们专注于这些目标以确保人类的整体生存。我们组织的关键目标是带来希望、安全、文明，从而保障幸存者的生存，并尽可能提供繁衍的可能性。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"Printed Scientist's Journal - IMPORTANT INFORMATION Instructions for "
"Survivors"
msgid_plural ""
"Printed Scientist's Journal - IMPORTANT INFORMATION Instructions for "
"Survivorss"
msgstr[0] "印刷版科学家日记——重要信息 幸存者指南"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Printed Scientist's Journal - IMPORTANT
#. INFORMATION Instructions for Survivors"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"If you have not found any of BL9 Safety Bases, you need to find at least one of them, this is important. If you have not found Strange Merchant, you need to find at least one of his transmitters to call him to trade, to answer your questions, this is important. If you are in any of BL9 Safety Bases currently, you need to talk to Base Android for her to answer your questions as well via her built-in system which stores categorized various optional intel along with journals which she can read which we have collected. They are optional to read honestly, but I suggest you to read them if you care more than just about loot from structures of our enemies in general. In order to explore BL9 locations safely, YOU SHOULD ASK BASE ANDROID ABOUT ORDER OF EXPLORATION when talking to her, this is important.\n"
" \n"
"    Initial BL9 recipes for BL9 weapons ammo, for BL9 melee weapons are unlocked whereas stronger versions are unlocked upon reaching particular levels of fabrication along with mechanics that are 5 of each along with 8 of each. So first two tiers of BL9-infused goods are sold by BL9 Strange Merchant. He sells them for Gold, Platinum Coins Combinations, which can be crafted via BL9 recipes from normal Gold, Platinum Coins which you can find when killing enemies, clearing BL9 locations. To unlock sci-fi ranged weapons, sci-fi melee weapons with unique effects to use against enemies, sci-fi armor, artifacts that grant mutually inclusive mutations that improve stats, skills, abilities, along with third tier of more common weapons that you can buy from Strange Merchant, craft, BL9 locations should be fully explored.\n"
" \n"
"    If we want to 'unfuck', save us, give us a guarantee to survive, live, love, procreate, you need to find Shield Generator which I have devised. This valuable machine is located in Mobile 'Alliance' Base. Bring it to BL9 Safety Base Android system which upon your orders according to how I have programmed it will activate Shield Generator to generate a Protective Shield hopefully. May God keep you, keep all of us safe, bring you, bring all of us luck hopefully as well"
msgstr ""
"如果你尚未找到任何BL9安全基地，你需要至少找到一个，这很重要。如果你尚未找到奇异商人，你需要至少找到一台他的发射器来召唤他进行交易、解答你的疑问，这很重要。如果你当前身处任何BL9安全基地，你需要与基地安卓机器人交谈，通过她内置的系统（存储了分类的各种可选情报以及她可以阅读的日志——这些是我们收集的）来获取答案。老实说，阅读这些是可选的，但如果你关心的不仅仅是敌人建筑中的战利品，我建议你阅读它们。为了安全探索BL9地点，当你与她交谈时，你应该向基地安卓机器人询问探索顺序，这很重要。\n"
"\n"
"初始的BL9武器弹药配方、BL9近战武器配方已解锁，而更强版本会在达到特定制造等级时解锁，同时解锁的机制包括每种各5个和每种各8个。因此，前两阶的BL9灌注商品由BL9奇异商人出售。他用金币、铂金币组合来交易这些商品，这些组合可以通过BL9配方用普通金币、铂金币制作——你可以在击杀敌人、清理BL9地点时找到它们。要解锁科幻远程武器、具有独特效果用于对抗敌人的科幻近战武器、科幻装甲、赋予互斥突变以提升属性、技能、能力的遗物，以及可以从奇异商人处购买、制作的第三阶更常见武器，BL9地点应被完全探索。\n"
"\n"
"如果我们想要“拨乱反正”、拯救我们、给我们生存、生活、相爱、繁衍的保障，你需要找到我设计的护盾发生器。这台宝贵的机器位于移动“联盟”基地中。将其带到BL9安全基地的安卓系统，根据我的编程，它会在你的指令下激活护盾发生器，希望能生成一个防护盾。愿上帝保佑你、保佑我们所有人安全，并带给你、带给我们所有人好运。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Printed Subject5's Journal - A Worldview of Love Along With Hope"
msgid_plural ""
"Printed Subject5's Journal - A Worldview of Love Along With Hopes"
msgstr[0] "打印版实验体5号的日志——一份爱与希望的世界观"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Printed Subject5's Journal - A Worldview of Love
#. Along With Hope"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"This Cataclysm, mutants, weird creatures, bandits, aliens, cults, really vile organizations, 'Alliance', all of this changes us with time. Survival becomes our main priority. We kill, we destroy, we don't trust anyone. Some forget what conscience is even. There is still a hope, many of these horrors or microorganisms can be used to our advantage, such as equipment based on alien technologies, creating healthy mutations or drugs based on modified microorganisms to make them benign, to fend off anything that corrupts us.\n"
" \n"
"    I don't know if we can still love or have children, but we must try, we all must try. I believe that we have a tiny bit of God's energy within us. With it we don't get entirely corrupted by vile sources, retaining our humane side. Based on this, we need to survive, to ascertain that ideas of good, hope, ethics, love will not be obsolete as well"
msgstr ""
"这场灾变、突变体、怪异生物、土匪、外星人、邪教、真正邪恶的组织、“联盟”，所有这些都随时间改变着我们。生存成为我们的首要任务。我们杀戮、我们破坏、我们不信任任何人。有些人甚至忘记了良知是什么。但仍有希望，许多这些恐怖事物或微生物可以被我们利用，例如基于外星科技的装备，创造健康的突变或基于改良微生物的药物，使它们变得良性，以抵御任何腐蚀我们的东西。\n"
"\n"
"我不知道我们是否还能相爱或生育孩子，但我们必须尝试，我们都必须尝试。我相信我们体内蕴藏着一丝上帝的能量。凭借它，我们不会完全被邪恶源头腐蚀，保留我们人性的一面。基于此，我们需要生存下去，以确保善良、希望、道德、爱的理念不会过时。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Agent's Notes - Part 1 - Strange Trader"
msgid_plural "Agent's Notes - Part 1 - Strange Traders"
msgstr[0] "特工笔记——第一部分——奇异商人"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Agent's Notes - Part 1 - Strange Trader"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"So first of all, to help you with your endeavors, there is a strange trading"
" merchant or a collector of some sorts here around The Castle, the zealots "
"are not hostile towards him for some reason. He claims to be selling "
"`BL9-infused goods` in exchange for the gold coins from the zealots. I am "
"not sure, but the quality of these seemed good to me upon first glance, but "
"my job here is being a spy and not really going all-guns blazing unless I'm "
"spotted..."
msgstr ""
"那么首先，为了协助你的努力，城堡附近有一位奇异的贸易商人或某种收藏家——狂热者们出于某种原因对他并不敌对。他声称出售“BL9灌注商品”以换取狂热者的金币。我不太确定，但乍看之下这些商品的质量似乎不错，不过我在这里的任务是充当间谍，除非被发现，否则不会全力开火……"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "BL9 Guide - Part 1 - Teleporter"
msgid_plural "BL9 Guide - Part 1 - Teleporters"
msgstr[0] "BL9指南——第一部分——传送器"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'BL9 Guide - Part 1 - Teleporter'}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"Good to see you still intact, adventurer - activate the teleporter right "
"HERE so that you'll be able to come back here instantly once you reach the "
"end of the Castle (make sure to survive, hopefully) with a special "
"teleporter item"
msgstr "很高兴看到你依然完好无损，冒险者——立即在此激活传送器，这样一旦你到达城堡尽头（确保生存，希望如此），就能通过特殊的传送器物品瞬间返回这里"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "BL9 Guide - Part 2 - Strange Trader"
msgid_plural "BL9 Guide - Part 2 - Strange Traders"
msgstr[0] "BL9指南——第二部分——奇异商人"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'BL9 Guide - Part 2 - Strange Trader'}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"The Strange Trader is the first key NPC of this mod (you find him in The "
"Castle, The Island, various BL9 biomes and structures) - he sells "
"BL9-infused goods of 2 tiers to you for GOLD and PLATINUM coins COMBINATIONS"
" (you automatically acquire the recipes to craft these) GComb and PComb "
"respectively. TALK to the Merchant to acquire your first basic handgun along"
" with the special soldering iron to repair BL9 items. The coins - you "
"collect them from enemies as well as by finding randomly scattered treasures"
" throughout the mod"
msgstr ""
"奇异商人是本模组的第一个关键NPC（你可以在城堡、岛屿、各种BL9生态区和建筑中找到他）——他向你出售两阶的BL9灌注商品，换取金币和铂金币组合（你会自动获得制作这些组合的配方），分别是GComb和PComb。与商人交谈以获得你的第一把基础手枪以及用于修复BL9物品的特殊焊枪。这些硬币——你可以从敌人那里收集，也可以通过在整个模组中随机散落的宝藏找到。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Agent's Notes - Part 2 - Through the Guard Rooms"
msgid_plural "Agent's Notes - Part 2 - Through the Guard Roomss"
msgstr[0] "特工笔记——第二部分——穿过警卫室"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Agent's Notes - Part 2 - Through the Guard
#. Rooms"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"In order to infiltrate The Castle you must go through multiple outside "
"constructions and the Guard Rooms which are filled with armed zealots, which"
" should not surprise you that much because they have kinda realized that "
"there is some kind of a breach caused by us..."
msgstr "为了潜入城堡，你必须穿过多个外部建筑和守卫室，那里满是武装狂热分子——这应该不会让你太惊讶，因为他们已经多少意识到我们造成的某种入侵……"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "BL9 Guide - Part 3 - Crafting Ammo and Melee Weapons"
msgid_plural "BL9 Guide - Part 3 - Crafting Ammo and Melee Weaponss"
msgstr[0] "BL9 指南 - 第3部分 - 制作弹药与近战武器"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'BL9 Guide - Part 3 - Crafting Ammo and Melee
#. Weapons'}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"Crafting is an important part of BL9 - you are able to craft many unique "
"ammo types and very handy melee weapons (and even a sci-fi tier of ammo for "
"sci-fi weapons, but that's a long way for you to go). The recipes for "
"initial tier are unlocked AUTOMATICALLY whereas further are unlocked upon "
"reaching a certain level in fabrication and mechanics which are level 5 of "
"each then level 8 of each - to craft each weapon you need to have generic "
"and rare materials which you'll come across as you play the mod"
msgstr ""
"制作是BL9的重要组成部分——你可以制作许多独特的弹药类型和非常顺手的近战武器（甚至还有科幻武器的科幻级别弹药，但这需要你走很长的路）。初始层级的配方会自动解锁，而更高级的配方则需要在制作和机械技能达到特定等级后解锁——分别是每项5级和每项8级。制作每件武器需要通用和稀有材料，这些材料会在游玩模组过程中遇到。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Agent's Notes - Part 3 - Into the Grand Hall"
msgid_plural "Agent's Notes - Part 3 - Into the Grand Halls"
msgstr[0] "特工笔记 - 第3部分 - 进入大厅"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Agent's Notes - Part 3 - Into the Grand Hall"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"Now you're approaching the Grand Hall, in order to get to the Throne Room, "
"first we must get into the Grand Hall which leads to the way to the Throne "
"Room, but the door leading to it is tightly locked and the key is hidden "
"somewhere. I'm yet to figure out WHERE, but I know that you have to go "
"through and explore the only accessible room here the door to which is "
"without locks"
msgstr ""
"现在你正接近大厅，要前往王座厅，首先我们必须进入大厅，那里通向王座厅的路，但通往它的门紧锁着，钥匙藏在某处。我还没弄清楚具体位置，但我知道你必须穿过并探索这里唯一可进入的房间，那扇门没有锁。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "BL9 Guide - Part 4 - Ranged Weapons Ammo"
msgid_plural "BL9 Guide - Part 4 - Ranged Weapons Ammos"
msgstr[0] "BL9 指南 - 第4部分 - 远程武器弹药"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'BL9 Guide - Part 4 - Ranged Weapons Ammo'}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"The ranged weapons in this mod are made to use special BL9 ammo types (BL9 "
"shot/BL9 shot MK ii, BL9 308/BL9 308 MK ii, etc) that is craftable ONLY "
"using the generic BL9 materials, BL9 samples of different tiers, from 1 to 4"
" with each tier of materials getting stronger. BL9 samples drop from BL9 "
"enemies. They are sold by Strange Trader too. They can also via recipes be "
"converted from one type to another"
msgstr ""
"本模组中的远程武器设计为使用特殊的BL9弹药类型（如BL9霰弹/BL9霰弹MK ii、BL9 308/BL9 308 MK "
"ii等），这些弹药只能使用通用BL9材料和不同层级的BL9样本制作，从1级到4级，每层材料都更加强力。BL9样本从BL9敌人身上掉落，也可由神秘商人出售，还能通过配方在不同类型间转换。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "BL9 Guide - Part 5 - Healing Herbs Along With Healing Sprays"
msgid_plural "BL9 Guide - Part 5 - Healing Herbs Along With Healing Sprayss"
msgstr[0] "BL9 指南 - 第5部分 - 治疗草药与治疗喷雾"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'BL9 Guide - Part 5 - Healing Herbs Along With
#. Healing Sprays'}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"In order to balance the strong and heavy damage dealing nature of the "
"monsters, I've created 3 tiers of herbs along with sprays that will heal you"
" instantly upon use and relieve a significant amount of pain without giving "
"you the painkiller debuff - from mild to the strongest healing herb along "
"with spray. BEWARE THOUGH - USE THEM SPARINGLY IN COMBAT. They give you a "
"STACKING DEBUFF for some time to keep everything balanced..."
msgstr ""
"为了平衡怪物强大且沉重的伤害特性，我创建了3个层级的草药及喷雾，使用后会立即治疗并显著缓解疼痛，且不会带来止痛药负面效果——从温和到最强效的治疗草药与喷雾。但请注意——在战斗中谨慎使用。它们会在一段时间内给你叠加负面效果，以保持整体平衡……"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Castlelan's Notes - Part 1 - I Welcome Thee, Little Moth"
msgid_plural "Castlelan's Notes - Part 1 - I Welcome Thee, Little Moths"
msgstr[0] "城堡人笔记 - 第1部分 - 欢迎你，小飞蛾"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Castlelan's Notes - Part 1 - I Welcome Thee,
#. Little Moth"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"Welcome to this magnificent, sophisticated structure, little moth. It is "
"great that you have arrived here. We are still in the middle of our rituals,"
" but so far it seems that The Great and Fierce Nevulion heard us and "
"bestowed upon us His great `blessing`. But you, you will not receive it, my "
"men will cleanse this place of your filth, you will NOT be able to defile "
"it!"
msgstr ""
"欢迎来到这座宏伟而精妙的建筑，小飞蛾。你能抵达此处真是太好了。我们的仪式仍在进行中，但到目前为止，伟大而凶猛的涅夫利昂似乎已听到我们的呼唤，并赐予了我们祂那伟大的`祝福`。但你，你将无法获得它，我的人会清除你在此地的污秽，你休想玷污这里！"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Agent's Notes - Part 4 - Blind Clawer"
msgid_plural "Agent's Notes - Part 4 - Blind Clawers"
msgstr[0] "特工笔记 - 第四部分 - 盲爪怪"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Agent's Notes - Part 4 - Blind Clawer"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"The key to the next room is hidden in a prison cell room, where a strange "
"creature named Blind Clawer seems to be locked up there. Be aware - it's a "
"ferocious tall blind BL9 augmented creature that is armed with mechanical "
"razor-sharp claws, it's quite strong but you WILL be able to defeat it, I am"
" sure!"
msgstr ""
"下一间房间的钥匙藏在一间牢房里，那里似乎关着一个名叫盲爪怪的奇异生物。注意——它是一种凶猛的、高大的、失明的BL9强化生物，装备着机械剃刀般锋利的爪子，它相当强大，但你一定能击败它，我确信！"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Agent's Notes - Part 5 - Underground Prison Cells"
msgid_plural "Agent's Notes - Part 5 - Underground Prison Cellss"
msgstr[0] "特工笔记 - 第五部分 - 地下牢房"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Agent's Notes - Part 5 - Underground Prison
#. Cells"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"It's good that you've managed to get through the ceremonial rooms, you see "
"now yourself that these zealots is a force to be reckoned with. In order to "
"go further, you need to acquire a key from the Underground Prison Cells, but"
" down there I've heard some strange buzzing sounds and sewer waters "
"splashing, be careful!"
msgstr ""
"很高兴你成功穿过了仪式房间，你现在自己也看到了，这些狂热分子是一股不可小觑的力量。为了继续前进，你需要从地下牢房获取一把钥匙，但我听说下面传来奇怪的嗡嗡声和下水道水的溅泼声，小心点！"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Castlelan's Notes - Part 2 - A Bunch of Flies"
msgid_plural "Castlelan's Notes - Part 2 - A Bunch of Fliess"
msgstr[0] "卡斯兰的笔记 - 第二部分 - 一群苍蝇"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Castlelan's Notes - Part 2 - A Bunch of Flies"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"So, you've interrupted our great ceremony and starting to massacre my "
"people. How rude and antagonistic of you, little moth, you seem to lack "
"manners. I guess my humble and welcoming servants do not really fit your "
"criteria, eh? A company of stinky flies for you, little moth - that is what "
"you are definitely going to appreciate!"
msgstr ""
"那么，你打断了我们伟大的仪式，并开始屠杀我的人民。多么粗鲁和敌对，小飞蛾，你似乎缺乏教养。我猜我那些谦卑而好客的仆从并不符合你的标准，对吧？送你一群臭苍蝇，小飞蛾——这绝对是你肯定会欣赏的！"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Agent's Notes - Part 6 - Through the Garden Labyrinth"
msgid_plural "Agent's Notes - Part 6 - Through the Garden Labyrinths"
msgstr[0] "特工笔记 - 第六部分 - 穿过花园迷宫"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Agent's Notes - Part 6 - Through the Garden
#. Labyrinth"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"I hope you're going strong. In order to go further you have to explore the "
"tricky branching Garden Labyrinth, somewhere there you'll find a key that "
"leads to the next room I presume. Note that there are 2 keys - you'll need "
"both of them - one you'll find for the construction in the garden that "
"contains the key for advancing further..."
msgstr ""
"我希望你状态良好。为了继续前进，你必须探索那错综复杂的分支花园迷宫，我想你会在某处找到一把通往下一个房间的钥匙。注意有两把钥匙——你都需要它们——一把你会在花园的某个建筑中找到，它包含用于进一步前进的钥匙……"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Castlelan's Notes - Part 3 - My Precious Garden"
msgid_plural "Castlelan's Notes - Part 3 - My Precious Gardens"
msgstr[0] "卡斯兰的笔记 - 第三部分 - 我珍爱的花园"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Castlelan's Notes - Part 3 - My Precious
#. Garden"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"You've gotten far, I have to admit this, but it all ends here, scum. You "
"won't escape alive from my mind-boggling garden full of creatures surprises."
" Besides, the annoying squashable bugs is not the only thing you are going "
"to see here in my Castle..."
msgstr ""
"你走得够远了，我不得不承认这点，但一切到此为止，渣滓。你休想活着逃出我那充满惊人生物的、令人费解的花园。况且，那些烦人的可压扁虫子并非你在我城堡里唯一会见到的东西……"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Agent's Notes - Part 7 - Infernal Room"
msgid_plural "Agent's Notes - Part 7 - Infernal Rooms"
msgstr[0] "特工笔记 - 第七部分 - 地狱之间"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Agent's Notes - Part 7 - Infernal Room"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"Alright, you're about to descend into the Infernal Room, the key to the way "
"to the Throne Room that can be accessed via the Grand Hall lies there, be "
"careful there!"
msgstr "好了，你即将进入地狱之间，通往王座厅的钥匙就在那里——那条可通过大厅进入的路径的关键所在，务必小心！"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Castlelan's Notes - Part 4 - A Friendly Reminder"
msgid_plural "Castlelan's Notes - Part 4 - A Friendly Reminders"
msgstr[0] "城堡领主笔记 - 第四部分 - 友好提醒"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Castlelan's Notes - Part 4 - A Friendly
#. Reminder"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"This is MY domain, this is MY realm! You seem to be forgetting this and "
"causing lots of mischief like an ungrateful bastard you are. My little moth,"
" your wings are still intact after the Infernal Room, eh? We'll see about "
"that soon enough..."
msgstr ""
"这是我的领地，这是我的疆域！你似乎忘了这点，还像忘恩负义的杂种一样惹是生非。我的小飞蛾，经过地狱之间后你的翅膀还完好无损，嗯？我们很快就会见分晓……"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Agent's Notes - Part 8 - The Bridge"
msgid_plural "Agent's Notes - Part 8 - The Bridges"
msgstr[0] "特工笔记 - 第八部分 - 桥梁"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Agent's Notes - Part 8 - The Bridge"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"I have some bad news - the location of the Castlelan is unknown to us, but "
"we are 100% sure he escaped via the underground passage in the throne room. "
"You MUST chase him down, you'll find the key to the bridge gates on the "
"OTHER side of the bridge in a series of rooms...be careful!"
msgstr ""
"有个坏消息——我们不清楚城堡领主的具体位置，但100%确定他通过王座厅的地下通道逃走了。你必须追上他，桥梁大门的钥匙就在桥另一侧的一系列房间里……千万小心！"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Agent's Notes - Part 9 - Infested Dungeon"
msgid_plural "Agent's Notes - Part 9 - Infested Dungeons"
msgstr[0] "特工笔记 - 第九部分 - 感染地牢"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Agent's Notes - Part 9 - Infested Dungeon"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"So far I've managed to receive enough intel to determine what else our crazy"
" castlelan has got up his sleeve. Below you there is an old dungeon that "
"seems to be infested with these Crawlers and God knows what else, upon "
"reaching the end of it you'll descend into the Castle's sewer system..."
msgstr ""
"目前我已收集到足够情报，能确定我们疯狂的城堡领主还藏着什么把戏。你下方是一座古老的地牢，似乎爬满了这些潜行者，天知道还有什么。抵达尽头后，你将进入城堡的下水道系统……"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Castlelan's Notes - Part 5 - My Defiled Dungeon"
msgid_plural "Castlelan's Notes - Part 5 - My Defiled Dungeons"
msgstr[0] "城堡领主笔记 - 第五部分 - 我受玷污的地牢"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Castlelan's Notes - Part 5 - My Defiled
#. Dungeon"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"Oh, while you're at it I would greatly appreciate it, little moth, if you "
"clean the old dungeon below off my miserable insects' filth, they've got a "
"bit out of control...one of my Right Hands will reward you GREATLY for "
"this..."
msgstr ""
"哦，既然你在这儿，小飞蛾，如果你能清理掉下面旧地牢里我那些可怜虫子的污秽，我会非常感激的，它们有点失控了……我的一个右臂会为此重重奖赏你的……"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Agent's Notes - Part 10 - The Assassin"
msgid_plural "Agent's Notes - Part 10 - The Assassins"
msgstr[0] "特工笔记 - 第十部分 - 刺客"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Agent's Notes - Part 10 - The Assassin"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"You are in the sewers - great, though BEWARE, Castlelan is not joking about "
"one of his Right Hands, it's not a mere crazed cultist. It is a tall lizard-"
"skinned incredibly agile and deadly creature that is capable of hiding in "
"the shadows, one of `THEIR` bioweapons it seems. It guards the path to the "
"mines below, use your wits and skills to DESTROY it!"
msgstr ""
"你在下水道里——很好，但要小心，卡斯泰兰关于他一个右臂的话可不是开玩笑，那不仅仅是个疯狂的邪教徒。那是一只高个子、蜥蜴皮肤、极其敏捷且致命的生物，能够隐藏在阴影中，似乎是`他们`的生物武器之一。它守卫着通往下方矿井的道路，用你的智慧和技能摧毁它！"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Castlelan's Notes - Part 6 - One of My Right Hands"
msgid_plural "Castlelan's Notes - Part 6 - One of My Right Handss"
msgstr[0] "卡斯泰兰的笔记 - 第六部分 - 我的一个右臂"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Castlelan's Notes - Part 6 - One of My Right
#. Hands"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"My servants, oh my loyal servants, you can't even conceive of how much they "
"love and adore me for bringing Nevulion's blessings to them! They even love "
"YOU now, little moth, so much that one of my Right Hands wants to personally"
" assess your strength and skills..."
msgstr ""
"我的仆人们，哦，我忠诚的仆人们，你们甚至无法想象他们多么热爱和崇拜我，因为我将内维利恩的祝福带给了他们！他们现在甚至也爱你了，小飞蛾，以至于我的一个右臂想亲自评估你的力量和技能……"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Agent's Notes - Part 11 - The Furnace"
msgid_plural "Agent's Notes - Part 11 - The Furnaces"
msgstr[0] "特工笔记 - 第十一部分 - 熔炉"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Agent's Notes - Part 11 - The Furnace"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"The next room leads to The Furnace, as far as I'm aware, there are 2 giant "
"cages inside...I guess another horrible bioweapon of `THEM`, do your BEST to"
" kill whatever you find there!"
msgstr "下一个房间通向熔炉，据我所知，里面有两个巨大的笼子……我猜是`他们`的另一个可怕生物武器，尽你所能杀死你在那里发现的任何东西！"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Castlelan's Notes - Part 7 - My Precious Furnace"
msgid_plural "Castlelan's Notes - Part 7 - My Precious Furnaces"
msgstr[0] "卡斯泰兰的笔记 - 第七部分 - 我珍贵的熔炉"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Castlelan's Notes - Part 7 - My Precious
#. Furnace"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"I'm starting to wonder what it takes for you to end just like any little "
"moth - burning and turning into dust entirely upon flying to the nearest "
"torch...the next room is my personal Furnace where I smelt ores found in the"
" mines AND the ruins. Lest someone should steal my ores I've got two good "
"barbaric bouncers...they WILL treat you accordingly, little moth..."
msgstr ""
"我开始好奇，你需要什么才能像任何小飞蛾一样终结——飞向最近的火焰，燃烧并完全化为灰烬……下一个房间是我个人的熔炉，我在那里冶炼矿井和废墟中找到的矿石。为了防止有人偷走我的矿石，我安排了两个野蛮的好保镖……他们会好好招待你的，小飞蛾……"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Agent's Notes - Part 12 - The Sand Ruins"
msgid_plural "Agent's Notes - Part 12 - The Sand Ruinss"
msgstr[0] "特工笔记 - 第十二部分 - 沙之废墟"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Agent's Notes - Part 12 - The Sand Ruins"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"Upstairs a series of undeground sand ruins awaits you, we believe that it is"
" one of the places from which cultists search for ores and precious gems, "
"they are all aware of your presence..."
msgstr "楼上有一系列地下沙土遗迹等着你，我们相信那是邪教徒寻找矿石与珍贵宝石的地点之一，他们全都知晓你的存在……"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Castlelan's Notes - Part 8 - You Are THAT Stubborn?"
msgid_plural "Castlelan's Notes - Part 8 - You Are THAT Stubborn?s"
msgstr[0] "卡斯托兰笔记 - 第八部分 - 你就这么固执吗？"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Castlelan's Notes - Part 8 - You Are THAT
#. Stubborn?"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"ENOUGH, STOP IT! How about you just STOP and GIVE UP YOURSELF until you are "
"brutally maimed at the hands of my servants? I've warned you before, little "
"moth, but now I am being SERIOUS, you won't get out of this dungeon alive, "
"entire horde of my heavily armed servants awaits you there! Trust me - they "
"WILL fight as fiercely, as ferociously as they can to pluck and devour your "
"teeny weeny wings, little moth!"
msgstr ""
"够了，停下！不如你就此止步，主动投降，直到被我的仆从们残忍地肢解？我曾警告过你，小飞蛾，但这次我是认真的——你无法活着离开这座地牢，我全副武装的仆从大军正在那里等着你！相信我——他们会竭尽全力、凶猛地战斗，只为拔下并吞噬你那微不足道的翅膀，小飞蛾！"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Agent's Notes - Part 13 - The Castlelan"
msgid_plural "Agent's Notes - Part 13 - The Castlelans"
msgstr[0] "特工笔记 - 第十三部分 - 卡斯托兰"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Agent's Notes - Part 13 - The Castlelan"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"You're getting there. In order to reach The Castlelan and put an exclamation"
" mark to everything that had led to this point you will have to cross the "
"bridge leading to the tower of The Castle where the madman ran away from "
"you, stop him, you can!"
msgstr "你快要到了。为了抵达卡斯托兰，并为一切导致此刻的事件画上句号，你必须穿过那座通往城堡塔楼的桥，那个疯子就是从那里逃走的。阻止他，你能做到！"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Castlelan's Notes - Part 9 - Nevulion is ONE With ME!"
msgid_plural "Castlelan's Notes - Part 9 - Nevulion is ONE With ME!s"
msgstr[0] "卡斯托兰笔记 - 第九部分 - 内弗利昂与我合而为一！"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Castlelan's Notes - Part 9 - Nevulion is ONE
#. With ME!"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"I have ascended into HIS realm, I could feel his might and power - not just "
"his blessing but a magical empowerment, a truly blissful feeling! I quenched"
" my thirst for power, little moth, but now I am HUNGRY! Hungry for blood, "
"your blood especially - I expect you in the tower to send you to Nevulion's "
"realm so he can TORMENT your vile soul endlessly!"
msgstr ""
"我已升入祂的领域，能感受到祂的威能与力量——不仅是祂的祝福，更是一种魔法赋能，真是极乐之感！我满足了对力量的渴望，小飞蛾，但现在我饿了！渴望着鲜血，尤其是你的血——我期待在塔楼见到你，将你送入内弗利昂的领域，让祂无尽折磨你那卑劣的灵魂！"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Agent's Notes - Part 14 - The Island"
msgid_plural "Agent's Notes - Part 14 - The Islands"
msgstr[0] "特工笔记 - 第十四部分 - 岛屿"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Agent's Notes - Part 14 - The Island"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"Hmm, now that you have cleared The Castle next target would be a distant "
"heavily fortified island in the middle of nowhere...you have done TREMENDOUS"
" work here, venture into The Island when you are prepared for an even more "
"dangerous encounter with monsters...I will be waiting..."
msgstr ""
"嗯，既然你已清理了城堡，下一个目标将是遥远荒芜之地中一座重兵把守的岛屿……你在此处完成了非凡的功绩，当你准备好迎接更危险的怪物遭遇时，便冒险前往那座岛屿吧……我会等着……"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Printed Agent's Journal - Part 10 - 'THEM'"
msgid_plural "Printed Agent's Journal - Part 10 - 'THEM's"
msgstr[0] "印刷版特工日志 - 第十部分 - '他们'"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Printed Agent's Journal - Part 10 - 'THEM'"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"So now I believe that you can guess `THEIR` plan - to create an army of perfectly obedient bio-soldiers to eradicate anyone that stands on their way and conquer these lands and try to take on the other regions, maybe even the whole world \n"
" \n"
"     They MUST be stopped! They are posing a threat to our and other remaining altruistic organizations. We do our best to help survivors, counter The Blob, establish SOME form of civilization, basic at least, spread our influence without spilling blood or turning everyone into controlled puppets..."
msgstr ""
"所以现在我相信你能猜到`他们`的计划——打造一支绝对服从的生物士兵大军，消灭所有挡路者，征服这片土地，并试图攻占其他地区，甚至可能是整个世界。\n"
"\n"
"     必须阻止他们！他们对我们及其他尚存的利他组织构成了威胁。我们尽力帮助幸存者，对抗`The Blob`，建立某种形式的文明（至少是基础的），在不流血或不将所有人变成受控傀儡的前提下扩展我们的影响力……"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Agent's Notes - Part 15 - The Way Through The Island"
msgid_plural "Agent's Notes - Part 15 - The Way Through The Islands"
msgstr[0] "特工笔记 - 第15部分 - 穿越岛屿之路"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Agent's Notes - Part 15 - The Way Through The
#. Island"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"You have reached the destination, I am glad to see you alive! Infiltrating "
"the Island you will come across camps, some small military structures - but "
"that's just the tip of the iceberg. The only way to get inside of The "
"Island's bunker and more elaborate structures is via water caves"
msgstr ""
"你已抵达目的地，很高兴看到你还活着！潜入岛屿后，你会遇到营地、一些小型军事设施——但这只是冰山一角。进入岛屿掩体及更复杂结构的唯一途径是通过水下山洞。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Master's Notes - Part 1 - So You Are HERE Now..."
msgid_plural "Master's Notes - Part 1 - So You Are HERE Now...s"
msgstr[0] "主宰者笔记 - 第1部分 - 那么，你现在`在这里`了……"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Master's Notes - Part 1 - So You Are HERE
#. Now..."}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"You have managed to enter `OUR` base where we conduct our activities - the "
"Militarized Island guarded by very well-trained biologically enhanced "
"soldiers armed to teeth. Plenty of them are heavily mutated having inhumane "
"strength and agility. That Castle - that was a mere cult controlled by an "
"archaic madman - I would have gotten rid of them myself upon starting our "
"conquest, but you've done me a good favor, your reward will be a bullet to "
"your head by one of my soldiers, survivor..."
msgstr ""
"你设法闯入了`我们`开展活动的基地——这座军事化岛屿由训练有素、全副武装的生物强化士兵守卫。其中许多士兵已严重突变，拥有非人的力量与敏捷。那座城堡——不过是一个被古老疯子控制的邪教——我本应在开始征服时亲自铲除他们，但你帮了我一个大忙，你的奖励将是我手下士兵赏你的一颗子弹，幸存者……"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Agent's Notes - Part 16 - The Water Caves"
msgid_plural "Agent's Notes - Part 16 - The Water Cavess"
msgstr[0] "特工笔记 - 第16部分 - 水下山洞"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Agent's Notes - Part 16 - The Water Caves"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"In order to get to the core of The Island, you must pass through the water "
"caves, as far as I know, it contains a mixture of `THEIR` soldiers and some "
"bioweapons, be careful there!"
msgstr "要进入岛屿核心，你必须穿过水下山洞。据我所知，那里混合着`他们`的士兵和一些生物武器，务必小心！"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Master's Notes - Part 2 - Think Twice"
msgid_plural "Master's Notes - Part 2 - Think Twices"
msgstr[0] "主宰者笔记 - 第2部分 - 三思而行"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Master's Notes - Part 2 - Think Twice"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"The BL9 - the sophisticated organism - WE have managed to exploit it, find "
"it's main strengths and expand them, eradicate it's weaknesses, make an army"
" of BL9 infused soldiers. You are taking on MY work, what I dedicated myself"
" to entirely! If you think you can come anywhere close to ending MY "
"organization, you are making the biggest mistake in your life!"
msgstr ""
"BL9——这种复杂的有机体——`我们`已成功利用它，发掘其主要优势并加以强化，消除其弱点，打造出一支注入BL9的士兵大军。你正在挑战`我`的工作，那是我全身心投入的事业！如果你以为能接近摧毁`我的`组织，那你正犯下此生最大的错误！"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Agent's Notes - Part 17 - The Labs"
msgid_plural "Agent's Notes - Part 17 - The Labss"
msgstr[0] "特工笔记 - 第17部分 - 实验室"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Agent's Notes - Part 17 - The Labs"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"The next rooms are hidden laboratories where `THEY` conduct their vile and "
"inhumane experiments. I've seen the bioweapons that are kept there and I've "
"been horrified - these are the most dangerous scums you've seen yet. "
"Incredibly tall flesh eating constantly regenerating abominations, it will "
"take many clips to gun these scums down, be careful!"
msgstr ""
"接下来的房间是隐藏实验室，`他们`在那里进行邪恶且不人道的实验。我见过存放在那里的生物武器，感到毛骨悚然——这些是你迄今为止见过的最危险的渣滓。它们是极其高大、不断再生、嗜食血肉的恐怖造物，需要消耗大量弹匣才能击倒这些渣滓，务必小心！"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Master's Notes - Part 3 - Scientific Experiments"
msgid_plural "Master's Notes - Part 3 - Scientific Experimentss"
msgstr[0] "大师笔记 - 第三部分 - 科学实验"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Master's Notes - Part 3 - Scientific
#. Experiments"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"Experimenting on BL9 proved to be a daunting yet very lucrative task. We've "
"learned a lot about it's origin, how it lives outside of a host and most "
"importantly - how exactly humans, animals and plants infuse with it, how it "
"`communicates`, compared it to The Blob and Mycus. My, my...these are mere "
"toys that are only capable of 7% of what BL9 can do and what it WILL do..."
msgstr ""
"对BL9的实验证明是一项艰巨但利润丰厚的任务。我们深入了解了它的起源、它在宿主外的生存方式，最重要的是——人类、动物和植物如何与它融合，它如何`沟通`，并将其与The"
" Blob和Mycus进行比较。哎呀呀……那些不过是玩具，只能做到BL9能力与未来潜力的7%……"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Agent's Notes - Part 18 - The Waste Disposal"
msgid_plural "Agent's Notes - Part 18 - The Waste Disposals"
msgstr[0] "特工笔记 - 第十八部分 - 废物处理区"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Agent's Notes - Part 18 - The Waste Disposal"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"In order to get to the other side of The Island, disappointingly, the only "
"way is to go via the Waste Disposal rooms below. The doors to it are locked "
"though, you'll have to find the ID card somewhere around here to open it, "
"advance further, I am sure it is somewhere around here..."
msgstr ""
"令人失望的是，要抵达岛屿的另一侧，唯一途径是穿过下方的废物处理区房间。但通往那里的门是锁着的，你得在这附近找到ID卡才能打开它，继续前进，我确信它就在这附近……"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Master's Notes - Part 4 - Still not Fascinated?"
msgid_plural "Master's Notes - Part 4 - Still not Fascinated?s"
msgstr[0] "大师笔记 - 第四部分 - 仍未着迷？"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Master's Notes - Part 4 - Still not
#. Fascinated?"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"You have witnessed our work of art - incredibly fast regenerating humanoids."
" You have also seen pinnacle of our work, provided to us by 'True Superiors'"
" organization, our allies. With enough time, we can make truly immortal "
"humans, extend humans' limits, you cannot even conceive of what power you "
"may achieve! Think of this - how about you stop while you still can? Turn "
"your back on this wanna-be-heroic bunch of fools and become a part of my "
"personal army. I give you an offer. We can establish The New Order together,"
" huh?"
msgstr ""
"你已目睹我们的艺术品——再生速度惊人的类人生物。你也见识了我们工作的巅峰之作，由我们的盟友‘真正上级’组织提供。假以时日，我们能创造出真正不朽的人类，突破人类的极限，你甚至无法想象自己将获得何等力量！想想看——何不在尚能回头时就此止步？背弃这群自以为英雄的傻瓜，加入我的私人军队。我向你发出邀请。我们可以共同建立新秩序，嗯？"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Agent's Notes - Part 19 - The Basement Passage"
msgid_plural "Agent's Notes - Part 19 - The Basement Passages"
msgstr[0] "特工笔记 - 第十九部分 - 地下室通道"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Agent's Notes - Part 19 - The Basement Passage"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"You made it through! Good, now in order to reach the surface of The Island "
"once again you will have to pass through a long basement passage, be aware "
"though - it is heavily guarded as far as I know..."
msgstr "你成功通过了！很好，现在要再次抵达岛屿表面，你必须穿过一条漫长的地下室通道，但请注意——据我所知，那里戒备森严……"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Agent's Notes - Part 20 - The Military Base"
msgid_plural "Agent's Notes - Part 20 - The Military Bases"
msgstr[0] "特工笔记 - 第二十部分 - 军事基地"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Agent's Notes - Part 20 - The Military Base"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"There is a huge structure after the military camps up ahead - a sleek hi-"
"tech military base - the reactors of which are powered by a strange "
"underground lava source below it, now we're dealing with more soldiers than "
"ever..."
msgstr "前方军营之后有一座巨大的建筑——一座流线型的高科技军事基地——其反应堆由下方一处奇特的地下熔岩源供能，现在我们面对的是比以往更多的士兵……"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Master's Notes - Part 5 - Don't Tread on ME"
msgid_plural "Master's Notes - Part 5 - Don't Tread on MEs"
msgstr[0] "大师笔记 - 第五部分 - 勿踏吾土"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Master's Notes - Part 5 - Don't Tread on ME"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"You have been given an offer - you chose poorly, foolishly - and now there "
"will be severe consequences for this in a form of my loyal soldiers. You "
"will not escape alive from the military base - what awaits you BENEATH is "
"BEYOND your imagination!"
msgstr ""
"你曾得到一个提议——你做出了糟糕而愚蠢的选择——现在，这将带来严重的后果，形式便是我忠诚的士兵们。你无法活着逃离这座军事基地——在基地之下等待你的，将超乎你的想象！"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Agent's Notes - Part 21 - The Secret Exit"
msgid_plural "Agent's Notes - Part 21 - The Secret Exits"
msgstr[0] "特工笔记 - 第二十一部分 - 秘密出口"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Agent's Notes - Part 21 - The Secret Exit"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"I've figured it out! The lava caves below which power up the reactor of this"
" facility play the role of a secret exit out of this place! Find the "
"keycards that open the room with the central reactor control laptops then "
"get out of there through the lava caves!"
msgstr ""
"我搞清楚了！为这座设施反应堆供能的下方熔岩洞穴，扮演着从此地秘密出口的角色！找到能打开中央反应堆控制笔记本电脑房间的钥匙卡，然后通过熔岩洞穴离开那里！"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Master's Notes - Part 6 - `IT`"
msgid_plural "Master's Notes - Part 6 - `IT`s"
msgstr[0] "大师笔记 - 第六部分 - `它`"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Master's Notes - Part 6 - `IT`"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"I must say I am impressed by your skills and wits and what has been saving "
"you from your imminent end, huh? The suspended cargo containers - ah the "
"scent of metal, weapons for my loyal soldiers and `IT` - ah, truly "
"fascinating! `IT` should keep you busy...`IT` WILL keep you busy!"
msgstr ""
"我必须说，你的技巧与智慧令我印象深刻，是什么让你从迫近的终结中幸存至今，嗯？那些悬吊的货物集装箱——啊，金属的气味，为我忠诚士兵准备的武器，还有`它`——啊，真是令人着迷！`它`会让你忙起来的……`它`一定会让你忙个不停！"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Agent's Notes - Part 22 - The Grotesque Amalgamation"
msgid_plural "Agent's Notes - Part 22 - The Grotesque Amalgamations"
msgstr[0] "特工笔记 - 第二十二部分 -  grotesque amalgamation"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Agent's Notes - Part 22 - The Grotesque
#. Amalgamation"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"So you've already heard of `IT`? `IT` - that's a grotesque amalgamation of "
"different creatures including a human spliced up together forming a very "
"dangerous and a deadly mutant. I believe that `IT` will be waiting for you "
"somewhere along your way, be aware of this and use this knowledge to not be "
"caught off guard!"
msgstr ""
"那么你已经听说过`它`了？`它`——那是一个由不同生物包括人类拼接而成的 grotesque "
"amalgamation，形成了一个极其危险且致命的突变体。我相信`它`会在你沿途的某个地方等着你，留意这一点，利用这个情报以免被打个措手不及！"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Agent's Notes - Part 23 - The Acidic Caves"
msgid_plural "Agent's Notes - Part 23 - The Acidic Cavess"
msgstr[0] "特工笔记 - 第二十三部分 - 酸性洞穴"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Agent's Notes - Part 23 - The Acidic Caves"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"Oh my...how could I be so ignorant? I completely forgot that 'IT' and other "
"nasty heavily mutated creatures had their own special domain deep down below"
" The Island. Environment which is very caustic and hostile to any normal "
"living being, where the 'Master' and his scientists placed creatures which "
"required 'special' conditions, be careful there!"
msgstr ""
"天啊……我怎么会如此无知？我完全忘了'它'和其他那些严重变异的恶心生物在岛屿深处拥有自己的特殊领域。那是一个对任何正常生物都极具腐蚀性和敌意的环境，'主宰'和他的科学家们将需要'特殊'条件的生物安置在那里，务必小心！"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Master's Notes - Part 7 - The Majestic Plant"
msgid_plural "Master's Notes - Part 7 - The Majestic Plants"
msgstr[0] "主宰笔记 - 第七部分 - 宏伟植物"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Master's Notes - Part 7 - The Majestic Plant"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"Ah, so you've come across the Caustic Plant Caves? BL9 experiments as you "
"can see led to creations of such grotesque but nevertheless beautiful "
"creatures like `IT`. However, infusing humans and animals only with this "
"peculiar organism is a true shame for someone who has been experimenting "
"with plants as well, there are more things to experiment on! This is how "
"Caustic Plant Caves were created - a truly dangerous environment where "
"plant-like BL9 beings live on their own using the best of their 'hive mind' "
"to breed and evolve..."
msgstr ""
"啊，这么说你遇到了腐蚀植物洞穴？正如你所见，BL9实验造就了像`它`这样怪诞却又美丽的生物。然而，仅仅将这种奇特生物融入人类和动物体内，对于同样研究植物的我来说，实在是一种遗憾，还有更多东西值得实验！腐蚀植物洞穴就是这样诞生的——一个极其危险的环境，植物状的BL9生物在那里依靠其'蜂巢思维'的最佳状态独立生存、繁殖和进化……"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Master's Notes - Part 8 - The General"
msgid_plural "Master's Notes - Part 8 - The Generals"
msgstr[0] "主宰笔记 - 第八部分 - 将军"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Master's Notes - Part 8 - The General"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"I guess that I really did underestimate you. Why would I even think that my "
"grotesque experimental amalgamations will be enough to finally stop you? You"
" need someone like you - my main general will take care of you with great "
"pleasure..."
msgstr "我想我确实低估你了。我怎么会认为我那些怪诞的实验融合体最终能阻止你呢？你需要一个像你一样的对手——我的主将会非常乐意亲自料理你……"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Agent's Notes - Part 24 - The Ruins and The General"
msgid_plural "Agent's Notes - Part 24 - The Ruins and The Generals"
msgstr[0] "特工笔记 - 第二十四部分 - 废墟与将军"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Agent's Notes - Part 24 - The Ruins and The
#. General"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"Once you clear the remanining camps, you'll come across The Island's ancient"
" surface ruins with more soldiers. Apparently `Master's` soldiers under the "
"control of his General established a little camp there fully expecting you "
"essentially. The General is a truly formidable foe and a force to be "
"reckoned with, don't let them ambush you!"
msgstr ""
"当你清理完剩余的营地后，将会遇到岛屿上古老的表面废墟，那里有更多士兵。显然，`主宰`的士兵在其将军的控制下，在那里建立了一个小营地，基本上就是在等你。将军是个真正可怕的对手，不容小觑，别让他们伏击你！"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "General's Notes - Part 1 - What's THIS Show for?"
msgid_plural "General's Notes - Part 1 - What's THIS Show for?s"
msgstr[0] "将军笔记 - 第一部分 - 这场戏是给谁看的？"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "General's Notes - Part 1 - What's THIS Show
#. for?"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"Your foolishness and stubbornness has no end, there's no stopping it! Now "
"even I am involved into this! You do know that you're prolonging the "
"Cataclysm with your actions? The BL9 is the only way to stop this and end "
"BOTH the Blob and Mycus, restore the civilization but ONLY with the worthy "
"society! Everyone else that falls short of our expectations shall be "
"eradicated!"
msgstr ""
"你的愚蠢和固执没有尽头，根本无法阻止！现在连我也被卷进来了！你难道不知道你的行为正在延长这场大灾变吗？BL9是阻止这一切、终结BOTH粘液体和真菌，恢复文明的唯一途径，但前提是建立一个配得上的社会！所有达不到我们期望的人都将被清除！"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "General's Notes - Part 2 - Our Plans"
msgid_plural "General's Notes - Part 2 - Our Planss"
msgstr[0] "将军笔记 - 第二部分 - 我们的计划"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "General's Notes - Part 2 - Our Plans"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"Once I deal with you, we will continue conducting experiments to make the process of infusing as controllable as possible. Any living creature that you can possibly think of - the synthesis of BL9 with human will allow us to form ANY bioweapon! \n"
" \n"
"     After that, we will start conquering local regions one by one - eradicating all the filth such as the Blob and Mycus and infusing every survivor that we find with BL9! The ones that will decline our generous offer shall be annihiliated!"
msgstr ""
"一旦我处理掉你，我们将继续开展实验，让注入过程尽可能可控。任何你能想到的生物——BL9与人类的结合将让我们能制造出任何生物武器！\n"
"\n"
"之后，我们将逐一征服周边区域——清除所有污秽之物，比如Blob和Mycus，并为我们找到的每一位幸存者注入BL9！那些拒绝我们慷慨提议的家伙将被彻底消灭！"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "General's Notes - Part 3 - The Power"
msgid_plural "General's Notes - Part 3 - The Powers"
msgstr[0] "将军笔记 - 第三部分 - 力量"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "General's Notes - Part 3 - The Power"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"This organism, it gives me a truly great might and power, I am stronger now "
"than I ever was! What about my old human limits? I don't see them anymore, I"
" am TRULY capable of ANYTHING! You will regret what you're missing out on, "
"fool!"
msgstr ""
"这个生物体赋予了我真正强大的力量与威能，现在的我比以往任何时候都更强！我旧时的人类极限？早已不复存在，我真正能做到任何事情！你会后悔自己错过了什么，蠢货！"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Agent's Notes - Part 25 - The Military Fortress"
msgid_plural "Agent's Notes - Part 25 - The Military Fortresss"
msgstr[0] "特工笔记 - 第二十五部分 - 军事堡垒"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Agent's Notes - Part 25 - The Military
#. Fortress"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"You are almost there, `Master` will not be able to escape anymore! Before "
"the encounter with him though you'll have to go through the remaining "
"military fortress on the Island, be careful! It is VERY heavily guarded, and"
" as you may have already guessed, you are an expected unwelcome guest here, "
"as usually..."
msgstr ""
"你快要到了，`主人`再也无法逃脱了！不过在遭遇他之前，你必须穿过岛上剩余的军事堡垒，小心点！那里守卫极其森严，而且你可能已经猜到了，你在这里是不受欢迎的访客，一如既往……"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Master's Notes - Part 9 - The Fortress"
msgid_plural "Master's Notes - Part 9 - The Fortresss"
msgstr[0] "主人笔记 - 第九部分 - 堡垒"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Master's Notes - Part 9 - The Fortress"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"You are truly surprising me now! You have eliminated even my most loyal "
"general - not much of a loss anyway. I'll have a dozens more if needed. The "
"final Island's fortress is standing tall - it will slow you down allowing me"
" to fully infuse with BL9"
msgstr ""
"你现在真让我惊讶！你甚至消灭了我最忠诚的将军——反正也没什么损失。如果需要，我还能有几十个。岛上最后的堡垒依然屹立——它会拖慢你的脚步，让我能完全与BL9融合。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Master's Notes - Part 10 - No Escape NOW!"
msgid_plural "Master's Notes - Part 10 - No Escape NOW!s"
msgstr[0] "主人笔记 - 第十部分 - 现在无处可逃！"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Master's Notes - Part 10 - No Escape NOW!"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"The process of infusion has been completed successfully! Now I possess the "
"power that I devoted myself ENTIRELY to, to make it as close to "
"extraterrestrial as possible! Niw that I can feel it - I realize how much I "
"underestimated it! You will feel it too - you will be forcefully infused "
"with it, either with or without your destruction, NO ESCAPE NOW!"
msgstr ""
"注入过程已成功完成！现在我拥有了我全心投入追求的力量，让它尽可能接近外星生物！如今我能感受到它——我才意识到我此前多么低估了它！你也会感受到的——你将被迫注入它，无论你是否被摧毁，现在无处可逃！"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Agent's Notes - Part 25 - The Master"
msgid_plural "Agent's Notes - Part 25 - The Masters"
msgstr[0] "特工笔记 - 第二十五部分 - 主人"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Agent's Notes - Part 25 - The Master"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"Above you `Master` awaits, he has already infused himself with the strongest"
" experimental BL9 sample, possibly horribly mutating and turning into a "
"barely human-looking creature! Be the victor in this battle for the SAKE of "
"humanity - 'Master' must NOT get away"
msgstr ""
"在你上方，`主宰`正等待着，他已将自身注入了最强的实验性BL9样本，可能已发生可怕变异，变成了几乎不像人类的生物！为了人类的存续，成为这场战斗的胜利者——绝不能让'主宰'逃脱。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "Agent's Notes - Part 26 - Thank You"
msgid_plural "Agent's Notes - Part 26 - Thank Yous"
msgstr[0] "特工笔记 - 第26部分 - 感谢你"

#. ~ Description for {'str': "Agent's Notes - Part 26 - Thank You"}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"YOU DID IT! I cannot believe that you DID IT! The horrible Castle and The "
"Island are no more! I can say now that you can be officially involved into "
"helping achieve mutually beneficial goals hopefully! Go to BL9 Safety Base, "
"this is important. You will be contacted there by one of our most "
"experienced scientists to instruct you further via an Android with a "
"wireless communication system. If you have already been there, you already "
"know everything, return there to continue bringing hope with your actions to"
" you, to all of us hopefully as well"
msgstr ""
"你做到了！我简直不敢相信你做到了！那可怕的城堡和岛屿已不复存在！现在我可以正式邀请你参与协助实现互利共赢的目标了！前往BL9安全基地，这很重要。在那里，我们经验最丰富的科学家之一将通过搭载无线通信系统的安卓机器人联系你，提供进一步指导。如果你已经去过那里，那么你已经知晓一切，返回那里继续用你的行动为你、也为我们所有人带来希望吧。"

#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid "BL9 Guide - Part 6 - Late-Game Explanations"
msgid_plural "BL9 Guide - Part 6 - Late-Game Explanationss"
msgstr[0] "BL9指南 - 第6部分 - 后期游戏说明"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'BL9 Guide - Part 6 - Late-Game Explanations'}
#: .\Items\lore.json
msgid ""
"Now that you have completed first half of mod, there is more to do. Proceed "
"or return to any of BL9 Safety Bases, from there explore, clear Guard Towers"
" of 'True Superiors' with Caves beneath them, acquire stronger gear. When "
"your main character with NPCs are strong enough, clear Mobile Alliance Base."
" Having destroyed Mobile Alliance Base along with having retrieved Shield "
"Generator you need to return to any of BL9 Safety Bases, talk to Base "
"Android, make Base Android system activate Shield Generator hopefully as "
"well"
msgstr ""
"既然你已完成模组的前半部分，还有更多任务等待完成。前往或返回任意BL9安全基地，从那里开始探索，清理'真正上级'的守卫塔及其下方的洞穴，获取更强装备。当你的主角与NPC足够强大时，清除移动联盟基地。摧毁移动联盟基地并取回护盾发生器后，你需要返回任意BL9安全基地，与基地安卓机器人对话，让基地安卓系统激活护盾发生器。"

#: .\Items\magazines.json
msgid "BL9 9x19mm magazine"
msgid_plural "BL9 9x19mm magazines"
msgstr[0] "BL9 9x19毫米弹匣"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'BL9 9x19mm magazine'}
#: .\Items\magazines.json
msgid "A plastic magazine made for BL9 9x19mm caliber ammo"
msgstr "为BL9 9x19毫米口径弹药设计的塑料弹匣"

#: .\Items\magazines.json
msgid "BL9 9x19mm MK ii magazine"
msgid_plural "BL9 9x19mm MK ii magazines"
msgstr[0] "BL9 9x19毫米MK ii弹匣"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'BL9 9x19mm MK ii magazine'}
#: .\Items\magazines.json
msgid "A plastic magazine made for BL9 9x19mm MK ii caliber ammo"
msgstr "为BL9 9x19毫米MK ii口径弹药设计的塑料弹匣"

#: .\Items\magazines.json
msgid "BL9 9x19mm MK iii magazine"
